Job_Title: Relocate to Wellington: Professor in Statistics and Data Science
Description: Wellington, New Zealand We seek a dynamic academic with a strong record of research in one or more branches of statistics and data science to provide academic leadership in one of New Zealand's most respected and innovative mathematical sciences Schools. The successful applicant will play a leading role in the development of the University's programmes and its standing in statistics and data science. The Statistics/Data Science group is well connected within the University, supporting opportunities to work with colleagues in biological, physical, health, social, earth and information sciences, engineering, business and the humanities. It also sustains strong connections with employers and researchers in the government, private and not-for-profit sectors, enabling work placements for students in our programmes. The appointee will undertake undergraduate and postgraduate teaching in statistics and data science. They will promote learning among students with a wide range of mathematical backgrounds. They will undertake supervision of postgraduate research students on both theoretical and applied topics, including students in the workplace seeking to advance their qualifications. They will maintain a research programme of international standard, in keeping with the University's emphasis on high-quality scholarship and will contribute to building on the University's engagement with stakeholders, including through externally funded research. The University is committed to building a diverse workforce and the School encourages applicants who are women, Māori, Pasifika and from other groups under-represented in the STEM sector. For further information please contact Ivy Liu, Head of School, School of Mathematics and Statistics ([email protected]) Applications close Friday, 15 November 2019. Victoria University of Wellington is an EEO employer and actively seeks to meet its obligations under the Treaty of Waitangi. Description: Opportunity to join at the beginning of a multi-year high impact transformation program We are currently establishing a key program at the Reserve Bank of Australia to deliver a new reporting and analytics platform that will be at the core of our economic insights and reporting. Description: As a senior member of our technical Data Architecture team, you will drive strategic direction across the Macquarie data landscape. You will work closely with and be a trusted adviser to our business and technology leaders and a strong network of data architects and engineers.  You will have the opportunity to be instrumental in building and evolving our data architecture framework and capabilities. You will enjoy taking on a wide range of responsibilities, covering everything from data governance and risk management, developing standards and principles, developing reference data architecture to assisting building data architecture capabilities in different business groups. Success will be measured by your contribution to business value and data architecture management.  All of your expertise and prior learnings will help you shape and realise our vision of a digital, data-driven insight-led business, providing a brilliant customer experience for our direct and partner businesses.  To excel in this role, you will be passionate about what Data Architecture should be and not constrained by what it has been. We need you to help us drive architectural change that transforms and optimises complex businesses with demanding requirements. It's important to be broadly experienced with the processes, applications and technologies common to financial services while being proficient in balancing disruptive innovation with the security, stability and governance required for a leading financial services business.  Extensive experience of working with a complex global financial services organisation is essential as this role is responsible for engaging, collaborating and influencing people across different business units and at all levels.   Your key accountabilities will include:  develop and implement the data architecture strategy for the Finance and Risk functions develop the enterprise data models develop data architecture principles, standards and guidelines and support their embedding within business groups promote collaboration between groups to drive data related best practices and capabilities, tool reuse, and strategic decision making advise, review and challenge groups in their implementation of the enterprise data architecture advise in the application of enterprise data architecture principles and standards within business and support groups contribute to the development of Macquarie's enterprise data strategy run/chair key architectural or governance forums advise on measuring and managing data architecture risk and non-compliance across the enterprise.  You will bring the following experience and expertise:  10+ years of IT working experience at least 4 years' experience in data architecture and governance experience in developing enterprise information architecture experience in developing modern data platform solutions experience in developing and implementing data governance, architecture frameworks and processes experience in developing and implementing enterprise and business group data strategies will have undertaken tool/technology selection (RFP/RFQ) experience in developing architectures with open source tools and technologies for big data good understanding and experience with the traditional DW architecture solutions solid background in data and analytics space ability to lead and influence across federated business groups proven track record in consulting, architecture, solutioning and implementation data/information modelling expertise at enterprise level a proven track record of successful delivery a strong team player who demonstrates flexibility and a pro-activeness to deliver to business outcomes excellent understanding of emerging technologies, and their associated impact on enterprise environments.  If this role sounds like the right opportunity to further your career, please apply via the link.  The Corporate Operations Group brings together specialist support services in Digital Transformation & Data, Technology, Market Operations, Human Resources, Business Services, Business Improvement & Strategy, Brand & Marketing and the Macquarie Group Foundation. Find out more about Macquarie careers at www.macquarie.com/careers  Macquarie understands the importance of diversity and inclusion - our long history of success has come from being different. At Macquarie we value the innovation and creativity that diversity of thought brings. The one thing we all have in common is our focus on high performance. If you're capable, motivated and can deliver, we want you on our team. We facilitate a range of flexible working arrangements within our teams. Talk to us about what flexibility may be available. Description: AustralianSuper is for all Australians and businesses; we put members first in everything we do with the goal of helping to create the best possible retirement outcome. More than 2 million members trust us to invest more than $170 billion on their behalf. A new and exciting opportunity has become available to join nbn as a Senior Associate, Data Insights as part of the BSM Analytics & Insights team, reporting directly to the National Manager of this business unit.  A bit about the role As a Senior Associate Data Insights, you will be part of a highly innovative team, working on interesting problems, leveraging cutting edge technology and wealth of data to build solutions to enable BSM to reach its targets. You will be integral in delivering unique insights about BSM operations, business customers and potential prospects. The role will see you design, implement and enhance new and existing data assets whilst providing recommendations on how to continuously refine and improve. Additionally, you will also support the implementation of data management solutions. This role will work closely with internal stakeholders including the BSM data team, members of the Chief Data Office, Data Governance, Master Data Management and Project Delivery. You will manage these touchpoints to support data-related initiatives and ensure alignment across the organisation. About Us  Mission Australia is a non-denominational Christian charity that has been helping vulnerable Australians move towards independence for more than 160 years. Every day we support people nationwide by combatting homelessness, assisting disadvantaged families and children, addressing mental health issues, fighting substance dependencies and much more. We are generously supported by our funders, partners and tens of thousands of everyday Australians, who make the work of our tireless volunteers and staff possible. Mission Australia is committed to keeping children and young people safe with zero tolerance of harm or abuse, and expect all our employees and volunteers to reflect this commitment.  Your Opportunity In this role, you will engage in and contribute to informed business decision-making and planning, supporting the broader organisation alongside the NDIA to achieve its strategic priorities, as well as delivering on regular reporting requirements to meet compliance. This position will cover Western and Far West NSW, and the Cairns LAC Area, as such the location is flexible. Solid knowledge of and experience in data analysis and generating advanced      Excel/PowerPoint reports    Understanding of the National Disability Insurance Scheme is extremely desirable    Experience in the use of data visualisation tools (such as Power BI) desirable Before starting work with us, you will need to undertake a national police history check, qualifications and referee checks, and have a clearance to work with children/vulnerable people. We have an innovative and supportive culture guided by our values of compassion, integrity, respect, perseverance and celebration. Description: Create an environment for the squad to grow together   Ensures the team lives and breathes agile value & principles   Ability to adopt a functional decomposition approach to analysis elaboration   First, a bit about ANZ At ANZ, everything we do boils down to ‘why’ – our purpose – to shape a world where people and communities thrive. We're just as focused on seeing our people thrive as well as our customers.  We are responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter the most, energising our people, eliminating waste and reducing bureaucracy.  ANZ NWOW Video  The purpose of the of the Data Service Customer is to create a system of people, processes and technologies (on premise and Cloud) / build for agility to provide data and capabilities for our customer facing business areas (including Australia and Institutional divisions) to create business and customer value by being in the moment with our customers.  As a  Journey Expert, you will optimise end-to-end customer journeys and improve the customer experience by devising innovative solutions, services, products or propositions  Also as a Scrum Master, you will help squads embed NWOW practices, facilitate ceremonies and foster effective team dynamics and operating rhythms. They work closely with the squad coach to improve ceremonies, rituals and engagement. Scrum Masters typically dedicate up to 30% of their capacity to their scrum duties and will ideally spend six sprints (or one business quarter) in the role before passing the ‘hat’ on to another squad member. You can also check out our Journey Expert persona or watch this animation to get an insight in to what a day in their life might look like.  Who are you?   A team player – You know we only win if we all win. You recognise and value the different perspectives and skills your colleagues bring. It is not about being a hero but jumping in and contributing to the successful delivery of the team’s mission   The customer’s biggest fan – You demonstrate a thirst for better understanding the customer and define the problem and develop solutions through their eyes   Comfortable being uncomfortable – You are comfortable with uncertainty and have the ability to effectively manage yourself through ambiguity and change   Continuous improvement junkie – You constructively challenge the status quo, look for better ways to do things and passionately advocate continuous improvement   Committed to your own and other’s growth – You strive to stretch and grow yourself and others by identifying your own development areas, seeking feedback and providing feedback to others to help them learn and grow everyday   A problem solver – You are energised by tackling complex problems and use critical thinking, your network, skills, knowledge, and available data to drive better outcomes for our customers and the bank   Commercially and Tech curios – I have a wide-angled lens. I am curious about what’s happening in the external market and innovations (technological and otherwise) and how we use this information to better inform our decisions and actions   Risk savvy – You build sustainable solutions that protect customers, stakeholders and the community   Accessibility and Inclusion Champion –I am committed to ensuring that our products, services, workplace and culture are accessible and inclusive for everyone, supporting participation, independence and dignity for our customers and colleagues. I will have regard to Principles of Universal Design in my own work, and when I work with colleagues and suppliers   What you bring to the Tribe:    Existing functional experience or expertise in one or more of the following disciplines: Business Analysis, Learning & Facilitation, Change Management / Implementation, Business Process Architecture, Performance excellence, Assurance, Marketing, Products or Channels   Ability to explore customer needs in a data-driven way, develop and implement innovative solutions, test the outcomes, and iterate   Domain or segment knowledge relevant to the tech area / tribe you are interested in joining (desired, but not mandatory)   An end-to-end appreciation of the customer journeys your tribe / tech area will be working on (desired, but not mandatory)   End to End delivery experience in ANZ and expert knowledge of internal ANZ delivery processes   Hands-on scrum master and Product owner experience with proven track record of enabling squads to deliver in an NWOW delivery model   At ANZ we aim to create an inclusive environment where employee differences such as gender, age, culture, disability, sexual orientation, family and caring responsibilities and religion are valued.    We work flexibly at ANZ. Talk to us and let us know how this role can be flexible for you.  This opportunity is located at 839 Collins Street, Docklands VIC and available at a Group 4.2 level  Further general information on our NWOW opportunities and selection approach is available in www.anz.com/careers. #GD4.2

About BHP  At BHP we support our people to grow, learn, develop their skills and reach their potential.  With a global portfolio of operations, we offer a diverse and inclusive environment with extraordinary career opportunities. Our strategy is to focus on creating a safe work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives, and where the capability of our people is key to our success.  Join Olympic Dam, a safe, reliable, globally competitive business delivered by our people. At Olympic Dam we care that everyone goes home safe to do the things they love. We believe Leadership drive culture and culture drives performance. All incidents are preventable and everyone has a role to play.  Come and be a part of this success. Our Operations One of Australia’s largest mines and a complex minerals processing operation, Olympic Dam, is unique in that we produce Copper, Uranium, Gold and Silver. The local township of Roxby Downs is an active and progressive community offering a variety of modern, well equipped housing, educational, health, sporting, leisure, shopping and cultural facilities.  About the role  Reporting directly to the Superintendent Underground Production, the purpose of this role is to collect and process information relating to equipment availability, load and haul fleets and ensure the most accurate information is available for analysis at all times. The position is based in the newly created Mine Integrated Operations Centre (MIOC) which centralises decision making and data collection for the underground mining operations. An opportunity exists to be part of a world-class control centre and make a significant contribution to ensuring our operations continue to improve performance in a sustainable way. The facility operates 24 hours a day, seven days a week and will see the introduction of state of the art technology and software for underground mining. Please note this position is based at Olympic Dam, operating on a 7/7 roster, with residential or FIFO to Adelaide options available. We are committed to providing a work environment in which everyone is included, treated fairly and with respect. We are an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from women and Indigenous people.  We know there are many aspects of our employees’ lives that are important, and work is only one of these, so we offer benefits to enable your work to fit with your life. These benefits include flexible working options; a generous paid parental leave policy; other extended leave entitlements and parent rooms.  How to apply Please apply online by 28 October 2019.

Versent is a rapidly growing Cloud Consulting organisation, specialising in AWS. We have offices in Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth and Singapore and have grown to over 300 people in just five years! We believe in bringing craftsmanship back to technology, because as technology artisans, we passionately care about the quality outcomes we leave behind. We've just started a new piece of work with multiple streams and we're looking to add to our Data practice. We're on the hunt for experienced Data Engineers to come on board. As our Data Engineer you will help deliver scalable, automated, repeatable ‘big data’ and analytic patterns within the AWS stack. Versent Data Engineers understand both data pipeline development, operations and management as well as delivery of automated data solutions that are ready for production operations.  Requirements  From a development or operations background (or an existing DataOps Team)  Understanding what getting something “done done” looks like (documentation, testing, operational requirements, continuous improvement of process)    Experience with big data tools: Hadoop, Spark, Kafka, Kinesis etc.  Knowledge of relational SQL and NoSQL databases, including Snowflake, PostgreSQL, Cassandra, etc.  Extensive experience with data pipelines and workflow management tools: Azkaban, Luigi, NiFi, Airflow, etc.  Experience with AWS cloud data services: EMR, RDS, Redshift, Kinesis, Glue  Previous exposure to stream-processing systems: Storm, Spark-Streaming, etc.   Experience with object-oriented/object function scripting languages: SQL, Python, PySpark, Scala, etc  Benefits Be part of a large body of work where you have the opportunity to join it right at the start. Because when people who care about their craft are given the freedom to explore possibilities without restriction, amazing things can happen. Job_Title: Executive Manager - Technology and Data Compliance
Description: Executive Manager - Technology and Data Compliance  This role is key to our Compliance agenda and will partner with our Group Technology and Group Data business to provide expert advice and guidance across all Compliance matters. You will frame business aligned strategic goals and initiatives whilst ensuring effective governance and risk management.  Reporting to the Head of Technology, Data and Operations Compliance you will - • Execute the Compliance functional agenda by proactively engaging and providing reliable and relevant compliance advice, training and monitoring solutions to address their needs. • Support and resolve critical compliance issues and develop appropriate solutions while adopting a continuous improvement approach in looking for ways to do things better to enhance overall efficiency and support to the business. • Supporting regulator interactions, including ASIC and APRA; and liaise with industry bodies to remain abreast of emerging issues and trends and to determine appropriate group policy positions.  What’s in it for me? This isn’t just a highly specialist role leading a respected team – it’s an exciting opportunity. You’ll work closely with strategies, projects and matters which not only give you a birds-eye view of the whole Westpac Group, but have a company-wide impact as well. And you’ll do that work with plenty of great benefits, along with flexible work arrangements to make sure the role’s the right fit. What do I need? We’d expect you to have extensive experience in a similar senior manager role either managing a Compliance, Risk or Legal team. Ideally, you will have experience Banking and Financial Services with a relevant tertiary qualification (eg Bachelor or postgraduate studies in Compliance). You’ll also need to have proven exposure across compliance frameworks, including the three lines of defence model, and financial services law obligations.  What’s it like to work there? We aim to provide one big, supportive team to help us reach our vision to become one of the world’s great service companies. As an equal opportunity employer, we’re proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion.  Westpac Group

Company_Name: NSW Department of Education and Communities
Description: Full-time ongoing appointment Location: 105 Phillip St, Parramatta About the Department of Education We ensure young children get the best start in life by supporting and regulating the early childhood education and care sector. We are the largest provider of public education in Australia with responsibility for delivering high-quality public education to two-thirds of the NSW student population. For more information about the Department of Education, please visit NSW Department of Education About the directorate The Centre for Education Statistics and Evaluation (CESE), undertakes in-depth analysis of education programs and outcomes across early childhood, school, training and higher education to inform whole-of-government, evidence based decision-making. Put simply, it seeks to find out what works best.  CESE’s three main responsibilities are to:          provide data analysis, information and evaluation that improve effectiveness, efficiency and accountability of education programs and strategies. collect essential education data and provide a one-stop shop for information needs – a single access point to education data that has appropriate safeguards to protect data confidentiality and integritybuild capacity across the whole education sector so that everyone can make better use of data and evidence. More information about the Centre can be found at www.cese.nsw.gov.au. About the role The position conducts and supports research and analysis projects led by the evaluation unit within the department. Our evaluations aim to provide evidence about the impacts of a range of education policies and programs. The ideal candidate will have a minimum 3 years experience working in applied data analysis roles.  How to apply The NSW Department of Education is committed to a diverse and inclusive workforce as an Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) employer. We encourage diverse applicants from a range of backgrounds to apply for roles in the department. To apply for this role, please submit an application by clicking “Apply Online” below. We are looking for you to demonstrate your competence in the focus capabilities as outlined in the role description in your answer, so please develop your response with this in mind. Note: the selection process will include a range of assessment techniques to assist in determining your suitability for the role. For enquiries about this role, contact Ian Watkins, Principal Data Analyst, CESE, Department of Education, at (02) 7814 1351 or by email to [email protected]. This is a child-related role. If you are the successful candidate you will be required to obtain a Working with Children Check (WWCC) Clearance number as a condition of employment (if you do not already have this). For more information, visit https://www.kidsguardian.nsw.gov.au/child-safe-organisations/working-with-children-check In addition, your employment may be subject to the Department’s Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check  to determine your suitability for employment.  If you are called to interview you will need to provide the following: Proof of Identity information Informed Consent Form  Declaration for child-related work Pre-Screening Questions:  Essential requirements Post-graduate qualifications in a quantitative discipline, such as statistics, economics or psychology. Demonstrated knowledge of econometrics (e.g. instrumental variables, regression discontinuity designs, difference-in-differences estimators), psychometrics (e.g. Rasch models, confirmatory factor analysis, test equating methods) and/or complex survey data (e.g. multi-stage sampling, survey weights). Demonstrated experience using statistical software packages (e.g. Stata, R, SPSS).Working with Children Check for paid employment Knowledge of and commitment to the Department's Aboriginal education   policies (Please find Aboriginal Education Review – Information)       Closing date: 20 November 2019 Note: A recruitment pool may be created through this recruitment process. Description: An exciting opportunity for a Data Scientist to join our Risk Management Group's Data Analytics Team within our Risk Management Group. The Data Analytics team is responsible for leading, developing and deliver analytics assets and capabilities for Risk Management Group.  As a Data Scientist you will apply your broad skillset across data and analytics to understand business problems, create insights and envisage practical solutions within the Risk Management Group across several initiatives.  You'll work with the team to assist us in defining and delivering a roadmap of data analytics initiatives that identify efficiencies and unlock insights/opportunities for the group. You will have access to large data sets, giving you the ability to make a tangible impact with your analysis and will be responsible for the creation and implementation of enterprise wide machine learning models across the Risk Management Group.  The role will see you working with the team and other stakeholders to continuously monitor, manage and improve existing models to ensure their ongoing efficacy and identify opportunities for improvements through tuning or new methods/models.   Day to day your main tasks will be but not limited to:  Identifying relevant data sources, cleaning and preparing data. Communicating complex concepts simply and translate outputs into actionable insights for associated business stakeholders through both verbal and written communication (e.g. reporting etc). Working closely with our Technology partners to implement best in class practices for Risk Management Group. Provide thought leadership on key developments in the data science industry and help to evangelise the capabilities in this area through regular stakeholder engagement and training. A curious and business outcome focused approach partnered with a problem-solving attitude. Practical experience with machine learning and statistics, as well as prior expertise proficiency working with large data sets (Big Data) and appropriate software (Cloudera, Spark, Jupyter Notebooks etc.).  The ability to be a strong collaborator and be comfortable working with business stakeholders to identify and shape problems to be solved with data. Proficient in using Python and/or R languages and in addition to this experience with NLP packages (Natural Language processing) would be a plus but not essential.   Additional Qualifications  A Graduate degree in a STEM discipline such as Data Science/Computer Science would be advantageous but not essential.   To express interest, please apply online today. Job Advert:  About the opportunity   This is an exciting role that sits within our Marketing and Innovation team. BP has just announced its intention to launch its own Loyalty program - BP Rewards - which will reinvent our customer's digital and reward experiences at BP. Your primary role will be to lead the production of analytics to inform the targeting and measurement of personalised direct marketing campaigns and provide key insights and recommendations for future improvements. In addition you will provide program level reporting for the newly launched BP Rewards Program.   Your day-to-day will include:   Campaign Analytics   Developing analytical models to inform the targeting of personalized direct marketing campaigns.  Analyse campaign performance using multiple data sources and optimising the operation of ongoing campaigns.  Develop regular reporting and dashboards, to assess performance against business goals - sharing results based on your 'test and learn' methodologies  Be an active member of the Analytics Community of Practise by sharing insights, approaches and demonstrating the value of analytics to broad audience.  Tell stories informed by analytics that are tailored to the relevant audiences   Business Analytics   Translating loyalty program data and analysis into reports and presentations for stakeholders.  Interpreting results & enabling business to leverage the results to maximise value.  Identify additional opportunities to optimise and further leverage customer and program data.  Assist the BP Marketing team with ad hoc data and analytics requirements  Form effective working relationships with external partners and internal stakeholders to improve operational performance.  Develop a detailed understanding of the operation of the BP Rewards loyalty program and how it is reflected in the data sources that you will draw from   Data Governance:   Ensure security and confidentiality of all data sourced within BP or from other confidential sources.  Ensure compliance with all legislation and regulatory requirements relating to data protection and privacy   To be successful in this role you will ideally have   Experience with CRM campaign analytics & marketing performance reporting  Implementing methodologies such as segmentation, propensity modeling, control groups and A/B testing.  Strong numeracy and a proven ability to analyse and draw insight from large volumes of data  Effective influencing and communication skills with a high degree of resilience and confidence in dealing with a variety of stakeholders.  Experience in building, operating and maintaining analytical models that support problem solving, decision making and optimisation.  A commercial mind set with the ability to assess both the short term and long term implications of decisions.  Experience using coding languages such a SQL, Python and R  Experience using visualisation tools such as tableau and Power BI   About the benefits   BP offers you a collaborative work culture and a company that lives and breathes our values of Safety, Respect, Excellence, Courage and One Team. We have a commitment to developing your career and reward our people with a competitive salary and benefits package. BP is an equal opportunity employer supporting inclusion and diversity in our workforce. BP Australia encourages women, people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander heritage and people of culturally diverse backgrounds to apply. Flexible working is encouraged at BP, so let us know how we can support you to maximise your work and home life. If this opportunity sounds like you, then we would love to hear from you. To apply, please click on the 'Apply' button below and follow the prompts.   Please apply online via the link provided.  About BP:We are a global energy business involved in every aspect of the energy system. We have 75,000 employees in 80 countries, working towards delivering light, heat and mobility to millions of people, every day. We are one of the very few companies equipped to solve some of the big complex challenges that matter for the future. We have a real contribution to make to the world's ambition of a low carbon future. Join us, and be part of what we can accomplish together. The Downstream segment has global manufacturing and marketing operations. It is the product and service-led arm of BP, made up of three businesses (Fuels, Lubricants, and Petrochemicals).  We aim to run safe and reliable operations across all our businesses, supported by leading brands and technologies, to deliver high-quality products and services that meet our customers' needs.  Disciplined execution of our strategy is helping improve our underlying performance, capture opportunities for further growth, generate attractive returns and create a more resilient business that is better able to withstand a range of market conditions; and create opportunities for future growth.

Full-time ongoing appointmentLocation: 105 Phillip St, Parramatta  About the Department of EducationWe ensure young children get the best start in life by supporting and regulating the early childhood education and care sector. We are the largest provider of public education in Australia with responsibility for delivering high-quality public education to two-thirds of the NSW student population.  For more information about the Department of Education, please visit NSW Department of Education  About the directorate The Centre for Education Statistics and Evaluation (CESE), undertakes in-depth analysis of education programs and outcomes across early childhood, school, training and higher education to inform whole-of-government, evidence based decision-making. Put simply, it seeks to find out what works best.   CESE's three main responsibilities are to: provide data analysis, information and evaluation that improve effectiveness, efficiency and accountability of education programs and strategies. collect essential education data and provide a one-stop shop for information needs - a single access point to education data that has appropriate safeguards to protect data confidentiality and integritybuild capacity across the whole education sector so that everyone can make better use of data and evidence. More information about the Centre can be found at www.cese.nsw.gov.au. About the role The position conducts and supports research and analysis projects led by the evaluation unit within the department. Our evaluations aim to provide evidence about the impacts of a range of education policies and programs. The ideal candidate will have a minimum 3 years experience working in applied data analysis roles.  How to applyThe NSW Department of Education is committed to a diverse and inclusive workforce as an Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) employer. We encourage diverse applicants from a range of backgrounds to apply for roles in the department.  To apply for this role, please submit an application by clicking "Apply Online" below. To apply, you will need to attach a cover letter (max. 2 pages) and your resume (max. 5 pages) in either Word or PDF format. Please address any pre-screening questions and any essential requirements. We are looking for you to demonstrate your competence in the focus capabilities as outlined in the role description in your answer, so please develop your response with this in mind.Note: the selection process will include a range of assessment techniques to assist in determining your suitability for the role.  For enquiries about this role, contact Ian Watkins, Principal Data Analyst, CESE, Department of Education, at (02) 7814 1351 or by email to [email protected] This is a child-related role. If you are the successful candidate you will be required to obtain a Working with Children Check (WWCC) Clearance number as a condition of employment (if you do not already have this). For more information, visit https://www.kidsguardian.nsw.gov.au/child-safe-organisations/working-with-children-check In addition, your employment may be subject to the Department's Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check to determine your suitability for employment.  If you are called to interview you will need to provide the following: Proof of Identity information Informed Consent Form  Declaration for child-related work Pre-Screening Questions:  Essential requirements Post-graduate qualifications in a quantitative discipline, such as statistics, economics or psychology. Demonstrated knowledge of econometrics (e.g. instrumental variables, regression discontinuity designs, difference-in-differences estimators), psychometrics (e.g. Rasch models, confirmatory factor analysis, test equating methods) and/or complex survey data (e.g. multi-stage sampling, survey weights). Demonstrated experience using statistical software packages (e.g. Stata, R, SPSS).Working with Children Check for paid employment Knowledge of and commitment to the Department's Aboriginal education policies (Please find Aboriginal Education Review - Information) Closing date: 20 November 2019Note: A recruitment pool may be created through this recruitment process. A recruitment pool is a group of applicants who have been assessed and identified as suitable for this role or similar roles, and who may be considered for a range of similar roles, including temporary, term or ongoing roles, over the next 18 months.

You will bring to the table excellent industry experience and passion for storage and data protection services. This experience will help you communicate possibilities and options as you further develop and communicate the strategy.  You will have experience communicating strategy at all levels of the organization, and be able to clearly articulate goals, objectives and plans in support of this strategy. You will have end to end accountability for the service - from architecture and design, through to service delivery and operations, commercial management and vendor management, and as such will be prepared to step into the detail as and when required. From digitising healthcare, to creating smarter cities and igniting our start-up industry, together we build trust in society and solve important problems. You’re collaborative and enjoy working in an innovative environment. You’re a problem solver by nature and want to work with a firm that values the kind of people who reimagine the possible for their clients and stakeholders. Description: A global leader in consulting, technology services and digital transformation, the Capgemini Group is at the forefront of innovation to address the entire breadth of clients' opportunities in the evolving world of cloud, digital and platforms. Building on its strong 50-year heritage and deep industry-specific expertise, Capgemini enables organizations to realize their business ambitions through an array of services from strategy to operations. Capgemini is driven by the conviction that the business value of technology comes from and through people. A multicultural company of over 200,000 team members in more than 40 countries, the Group reported 2018 global revenues of EUR 13.2 billion. People matter, results count. Learn more about us at www.capgemini.com Let's talk about the team:Our Insights and Data team helps our clients make better business decisions by transforming an ocean of data into streams of insight. Our clients are among Australia's top performing companies and they choose to partner with Capgemini for a very good reason - our exceptional people.The key objective of the Capgemini's Insights & Data practice is to work in a unique, pioneering and collaborative way with our clients to provide unique and customised opportunities to turn data into insights. We help our clients to turn their digital vision into a compelling Insights & Data strategy that delivers tangible, measurable value. We also help to renew their existing data estate - achieving cost and agility benefits on the way - while becoming a truly digital, insightful enterprise.  Let's talk about the role and responsibilities: The Consultant role is to be part of all activities within Capgemini Insight & Data(I&D) team. Such activities could be related to the integration of data across various sources into an organised and unified view. Or the use of data for Analytica or Data Science initiatives, bring better knowledge and insights to an organisations data while working with On-premise and Cloud platforms to achieve such tasks. The Consultants role see's good communication skills, problem-solving skills, and the ability to become self-aware of data best practices being critical to successful performance in this role.Some of your responsibilities will include:  * Conduct research on emerging I&D products, languages, and standards in support of procurement, development, security, and integration efforts in relation to the Cloud, BI, analytics and big data management.* Work closely with data analysts, data stewards, developers, data scientist and system owners in the testing of newly-incorporated databases and integration measures.* Communicate with developers as well as engineers to address issues in data patterns and architecture.* Build relationships with development and infrastructure engineering teams to gain an understanding of different data architectures and required functionality.* Adept in understanding technical requirements and convert them into data flows. Let's talk about your qualifications and experience: To be considered for this role you must have:  * University degree in computer science, computer engineering or equivalent Math's and Science Degree* At least 1-2 years of experience in the following:* Knowledge or Experience with SQL development, an Understanding of Stored Procedures and Functions.* Knowledge or Experience in one RDBMS such as MS SQL Server, MySql.* Knowledge or Experience of data modelling methodologies and concepts such as Kimball, database normalisation.* Knowledge or Experience in version control platforms such as GitHub, Gitlab, MS TFS, AWS Beanstalk.* Knowledge or Experience in cloud platforms - AWS, Azure, Google.* Knowledge or experience in programming languages, such as Java, Python, R, C++.* Knowledge or experience in Software development life cycle. Nice to have  * Knowledge of CI/DI DevOps practices.* Knowledge of Message Brokers Such as Jboss, Kafka, Amazon Kinesis, Azure Event Hub.* Knowledge or experience Big Data Technologies such as Hadoop, Cloudera, Spark, Scala.* Knowledge or experience in Machine Learning Platforms such as Knime,* Knowledge or experience working in Unix/*nic with Bash/Shell scripting. Please note due to the nature of our clients we can only consider Australian citizens. What happens next and what can we offer you?Interested? Passionate people are Capgemini's Ace of spades. We believe that every one of us is an architect of positive futures. We invite you to join us to discover a career that will challenge, support and inspire you. Working at Capgemini you'll find the rewards are more than just financial. Not only will you work alongside inspiring colleagues with a world of experience, but you'll also have access to great benefits including, salary continuance insurance, paid parental leave, education assistance, salary packaging, the ability to purchase additional leave; as well as discounts on entertainment, financial and wellbeing services, travel and shopping. Talk to us about working part-time or full time. Ranked among Ethisphere's 2019 Most Ethical Companies in the World (for the 7th year running!), our seven values are at the heart of everything we do - Honesty, Boldness, Trust, Team Spirit, Freedom, Fun and Modesty. As Social Innovators, we are committed to making a positive impact on the planet and our communities. Capgemini is a proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and all applicants must be legally entitled to work in the country the role is based out of, unless otherwise stated within the job advertisement. Proof of work entitlements and visa status will be required prior to and/or at time of offer. Successful applicants will be required to complete a security and reference checks prior to commencement of employment. Please note unsolicited resumes from employment agencies or other third parties will not be considered.  #LI-HA1

As a Senior Data Scientist, you'll guide an agile multifunctional team including a Junior Data Scientist, Domain Expert and a Data Engineer. Your role will be to apply your broad skillset across data and analytics to understand business problems, create insights and envisage practical solutions in areas such as trade processing and information technology.  Your broad area of responsibility will be to assist us defining and delivering a roadmap of data initiatives that identify efficiencies, unlock opportunities, and generate revenue. You will have access to large data sets, giving you the ability to make a tangible impact with your analysis. In return, you will be given support to expand your technical and domain skills.  As a Data Scientist, you'll work directly with our business units to ideate, prioritise and perform the initial feasibility checks on ideas to improve business outcomes, leveraging data and prioritising these ideas through benefits modelling. By determining appropriate analytical approaches to solving business problems, you'll identify whether these requirements can be achieved via existing internal or external capability or via engineering new solutions.  In addition, you will be responsible for:  sourcing and identifying relevant data sources, cleaning and preparing data performing modelling and analysis using charting, descriptive statistics and machine learning creating impactful dashboards and consumable insights using human centred design principles communicating complex concepts simply and translating outputs into actionable insights for business stakeholders defining and providing requirements to data engineers in order to automate data mentoring junior data scientists including reviewing code and analysis approaches.  To be successful in this role you will have some of the following skills/background and experience:  5+ years experience in a hands-on data science role - you are considered an expert and have either led a team or mentored more junior team members curious and business outcome focused with a problem-solving attitude evidence of having innovated and improved a business outcome using data, rather than just implementing a requirement experience in delivering the full lifecycle of projects from R&D through to deployment strong collaboration skills having worked with business stakeholders to identify and shape problems to be solved with data accessed and sourced data from a variety of systems using SQL and APIs expertise in cleansing, combining and processing data comfortable using Python or R practical experience with machine learning and statistics familiarity with data visualization tools (e.g. Microstrategy, PowerBI, Tableau, Quicksight, Qlik) proficiency working with large data sets (10m+ records) and cloud computing would be an advantage.  Ideally, you will have commercial exposure in a corporate, consultancy or start-up environment, and a financial services background is an advantage. Are you looking to start your career in the field of your studies or even something bigger? Our Professional Internship Program is a structured program run by qualified staff that offers students a career readiness program, industry mentor, and an internship in a professional environment. Upon completion of the program, you will be eligible to undertake an internship placement relevant to your field of study.  About our host companies:Our host companies are well established in Australian businesses. They offer a supportive learning environment that pays particular attention to learner's needs.They deliver bespoke, practical and fact-based solutions for the clients by combining proprietary tools and techniques to quickly bring transparency to organisational effectiveness, with experienced teams of rigorous, creative and pragmatic consultants.  Learning Opportunities: Some of the activities you could expect part of your intern role include:  Performing research and data sourcing Data analysis Data visualisations Data modelling (subject to the level of knowledge and understanding) Data wrangling   Please note: Responsibilities and detailed projects will be determined based on your educational background, interests, and skills. All activities will be under the host company’s supervision.  To register for the Program, you must be:  Currently studying or recently completed relevant into the IT/ Data Analyst/ Engineering Science field is a MUST Able to demonstrate English language proficiency or be a native speaker Knowledge on R, Python, SQL Programming language (through studies) Knowledge of data wrangling (exposure with data in CSV and other formats) Understanding of basic statistical methods for data analytics   About Eightfold Institute of Australia: Eightfold Institute of Australia is a nationally recognised training organisation - RTO Code 22577 dedicated to helping students and graduates to develop their knowledge, skills and abilities by providing Professional Development and Internship Programs. We provide you with actual industry experience in your profession and the skills to help you succeed in your career. Our focus is to ensure the program maximises your work-integrated learning experience. Fees apply for the program. Throughout the program, you will strengthen your employment prospects, improve your work readiness and general skills to help you toward future employment opportunities. Register your interest with our Professional Development and Internship Program. There is no better place to show what you’re made of – apply now!

Description: About Us The Endeavour Drinks Group ambition is bold, we want to be the world's best drinks retailer. We know that expectations of retail have never been higher so our transactions must be instant, and our services must be intuitive and personal. We are embarking on our next generation of growth, and we want you to be an influential part of it. Our family of leading brands is well respected and highly visible throughout Australia, New Zealand and the world; from Dan Murphy’s, our market leading destination drinks merchant, to our local convenience offering at BWS, and our Cellarmasterwines and Langtons businesses  with each of them commanding a leadership position in their respective category. The Role As a Senior Data Analyst you will be part of a team to establish a new retail analytics capability required to deliver our ambition to be customer and insight led business. As a team we support our merchandising, strategy, finance and operations teams in understanding product sales data and using this to create the best experiences for our customers through data and insight led decisions. Working with the broader Data & Analytics Team, you will be key in designing the end to end data modelling solutions to suit the needs of the business. You will engage with stakeholders to understand business problems and developing the ETL for the solution. You will be responsible for producing automation and monitoring at all steps of our analytics and tool construction, including integration, testing, deployment and infrastructure management. Key responsibilities in this role will also include: Independently design, development, installation and maintenance of a scalable database solution for the team Transition of datasets from legacy products and external data sources to our Google or Azure Cloud Platforms Development of data-set processes for data modeling, mining and production Collection, cleansing, merging and management of data from various sources across the business Build and maintain new data structures and design data processing systems A little about you You’re focussed on our customer mission and passionate about being part of a great team. Whatever you love - design, technology, engineering, you’re active in the community that surrounds it. You orient around doing what’s meaningful, purposeful and delivers value. You’re excited about being part of data transformation and passionate about our customers.  You have a proven track in developing tableau dashboards and a natural problem solving mindset to create solutions that suit the needs of the business. To be successful in this role, you will likely possess some of the following: Minimum of 8 years working experience as data migration/transformation/integration specialist Strong hands on ETL experience and strong SQL skills A strong technical understanding with business acumen Extensive experience in Data Conversion/Migration Projects Strong experience with databases, DB queries, able to manipulate data & understand impacts on performance (SQL, Teradata, excel etc) Demonstrated capability ensuring end-to-end solution designs meet the needs of the client, provide for a quality technical solution, and comply with architectural directions and enterprise standards Experience of working in cross functional teams within an agile delivery framework What's in it for you An attractive remuneration package Opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest and best minds in Australia Training and Education - We pride ourselves in helping you realise your potential and give you the opportunity to be innovative An exciting career - as our business grows, so do the opportunities for our Team Members If you meet a number of requirements (and not all), we encourage you to submit your application. As an inclusive, team-first company, our people are at the core of everything we do. As our Group continues to evolve, innovate and support our communities, we encourage our team members to do the same with their own careers, by providing ongoing opportunities to grow and make a real difference.  We value diversity and aim to create a vibrant and inclusive workforce which reflects the communities we serve.  Sound like your next opportunity? Description: Group: Corporate Operations Group  Division: Digital Transformation & Data  Recruiter: Chirag Bhojani This role sits within the Enterprise Data Management function and specifically the team that is responsible for building out the Enterprise Tools that are used to govern data across the organisation. The remit of the Enterprise Data Management team is quiet broad and you will utilise your previous Business Analyst experience and take on a range of responsibilities. This role has a focus on Data Quality and the implementation of a new Enterprise Data Quality Tool in Macquarie. As part of your day to day duties you will work with the Enterprise Data Management Team and Business Teams to shape our data governance processes and support other teams on their data initiatives and projects to ensure they are getting value from our data tool-sets. You will take the lead in document requirements needed in our Data Quality Tool to support the data quality process and help the business teams to define and implement data quality rules and providing best practice guidelines in data quality.  In addition, you will develop and deliver training material and templates to support on-boarding of the business community into our data quality tool. You will have a good technical background and happy to work with business teams to elicit requirements and manage our stakeholder expectations. As a core quality you will have a core understanding of data and how data quality is managed in a large enterprise. Experience working in a data quality role or within a data governance function is important and  hands on experience writing data quality rules and using enterprise data quality tools will be highly regarded. You are a self-starter that is happy to take on ownership of their deliverables and take the initiative to drive end to end outcomes. In this role you will be required to facilitate workshops and user training. In addition, you will also have a: Good understanding of data management principles and data quality.Exposure to data architecture or data modelling highly regarded.Business requirements elicitation and documentation.Use Case Design and User Story Development.Strong communication skillset and the capability to facilitate workshops and training sessions. If this opportunity interests and next career move, then please apply online.  Corporate Operations Group (COG) provides specialist professional services, human resources, workplace infrastructure, technology and market operations to Macquarie's businesses. The primary purpose of COG is to support and enhance the value of Macquarie through the creation of an efficient, scalable operating model. This is evident across the activities of each of the divisions which comprises of Business Improvement and Strategy Division (BIS), Business Services Division (BSD), COG Business Management, Human Resources Division (HR), Market Operations, Operational Risk Strategy and Support, Shared Services and Technology. Find out more about Macquarie careers at www.macquarie.com/careers Macquarie understands the importance of diversity and inclusion - our long history of success has come from being different. At Macquarie we value the innovation and creativity that diversity of thought brings. The one thing we all have in common is our focus on high performance. If you're capable, motivated and can deliver, we want you on our team. We facilitate a range of flexible working arrangements within our teams. Talk to us about what flexibility may be available.

With service in mind at every touch point, we take accountability for the role we play in securing and enhancing the financial wellbeing of people, businesses and communities. At CommBank you can be you!  Our Team The Direct Channels Operations team provides works across Financial Assistance Solutions and the Reset Program. Ensuring proper automation and relevant documentationConducting a consultancy function with the business to assess the decisions made from those reports and opportunities for simplification, including metrics definitions & projects ETAsCoach & build the right analytics capability across the business to best utilise the data availableBuild strategic solutions, including migrating all reports into Tableau following industry best practicesEmbedding strong data governance and long term data strategy. What You Will have 5+ years of experience in analytics, preferably in financial industry2+ years of experience of leading a team of Analyst and ManagersAble to identify and develop Talent, and foster a supportive and collaborative working environmentProficient in SAS and/or SQL and TableauSophisticated influencing & presentation skills to Senior StakeholdersCapacity to build rapport & engagement with the businessAbility to find the right balance between technical details vs. strategic team visionStrong understanding of regulatory and compliance requirements You. You demonstrate resilience in situations of organisation change, willingness and ability to absorb broader responsibilities, exercise proactivity and show initiative on key strategic projects, whilst building a culture of inclusiveness & high-performance in the team.You communicate your ideas simply and create clarity and know how to build and maintain a high performing culture.

Description: Let's talk about ME  We're not like other banks.  ME was created by the industry super funds to be different from the pack ­- and we're passionate about staying that way as we head into an exciting and progressive future. We are building a bank, a company and a brand that we can be proud of - but to achieve that, we need the best people.  To help ME get there, you'll challenge the status quo and share extraordinary ideas - and our size guarantees you'll have the opportunity, support and environment to be heard. ME's core purpose is helping all Australians get ahead - no conditions, asterisks or exceptions.  We believe everyone deserves the same opportunities in life, regardless of gender or identity, sexuality, ethnicity, religion or disability. This is why we're so committed to an equal opportunity workplace - because we know our success won't come from focusing on similarities, but by embracing and celebrating our diversity.  Let's talk about what you'll be doing If you love all things data, then, we have the job for you! You'll be exposed to the amazing things that ME is working on to help all Australians get ahead, such as building a new data warehouse from scratch (woohoo!), digital wallets and heaps of other exciting projects across our Hubs!  You'll be working with our amazing Enterprise Data team to ensure our data assets are designed well, captured for quality, stored for efficiency, documented for ease of use and delivered reliability! You'll create standards and controls that cover data definitions, master data management, business semantics and data modelling.  You'll work hard to create harmony across our data ecosystem to deliver outstanding benefits for ME!  To be ME, we need YOU!  As our newest Data Architect, you'll be joining a team of passionate and determined MEEPs who are paving the way for ME's data! You'll bring your expertise to the wider Data team and our hubs, by working solidly as a team player and sharing your knowledge. You'll thrive in a fast environment, that is experiencing significant change and transformation. You'll also have worked in an Agile environment previously.  You'll be a pro in enterprise data platforms (data warehousing, ETL, Data Governance and Quality, Analytics or BI). You'll also have a strong understanding of data quality, data management and governance frameworks and methodologies. Previous experience working in a Bank or highly regulated environment is preferred (but not a deal breaker!)  Perks! At ME, we believe that work should be a place that you can make the most of - and these are just some of the many reasons why people love it here: Popular culture - that's not a claim, we've got the data to prove it. We genuinely care about each other and work in an encouraging and collaborative environment.The whole package - sure, we're going to reward you well with your salary package - but there are also lots of other perks - including discounted Myki travel cards, free health support, conveniently-located offices, plus much more.Not afraid to fail? We embrace action-oriented people like you. That's right, you can make mistakes here and it's ok - so long as you learn from them.To be ME, we need you - we're building something really cool and you get to directly influence what that is.ProudlyME - our internal pride network - has a swag of initiatives that show support, education, and passion toward our team and customers, demonstrating that ME is a strong advocate on equal rights for the LGBTIQ+ community.Meet the Execs - our Executive team is fun and full of passion because we know great managers mean happy staff. Oh, and did we mention you get your very own ME branded High-top shoes? Now that's a reason to get your foot in the door.  I was born to play this role  If this sounds like the perfect job for you, why wait? Apply now by submitting your resume today.  Can't see a closing date on the advert? That's because we're pretty efficient here at ME and we may start looking at applications sooner rather than later, so if this role sounds like your jam, be sure to apply today.  Should an applicant be the preferred candidate, background checks (including police checks, reference checks, ASIC banned and disqualified persons and bankruptcy checks) will be completed prior to the candidate's employment being confirmed. The outcomes of the background checks do not automatically bar candidates; however will be assessed against the inherent requirements of the job.

Description: Job no: 583446  Work type: Full time - Continuing/Permanent  Categories: Accounting, Audit and Finance Full-time, continuing positionConvenient Melbourne CBDTake your career to the next step with RMIT About Us RMIT is a multi-sector university of technology, design and enterprise with more than 91,000 students and 11,000 staff globally. RMIT offers postgraduate, undergraduate, vocational education and online programs to provide students with a variety of work-relevant pathways. Our purpose is to offer life-changing experiences for our students, and to help shape the world with research, innovation, teaching and industry engagement. With strong industry connections forged over 130 years, collaboration with industry remains integral to RMIT’s leadership in education, applied and innovative research, and to the development of highly skilled, globally-focused graduates. The Office of the Chief Data & Analytics Officer supports and enables RMIT’s business strategy by leading and driving the data and analytics agenda for the enterprise. This involves being accountable and responsible for: Developing and implementing RMIT’s data & analytics strategy, and ensuring ongoing alignment with university projects and initiativesLeading information governance framework and activities across RMITDefining requirements and standards for data and analytics technologies to be delivered by Information TechnologyCoordinating and governing data management activities for analytics and reportingDeveloping and coordinating advanced analytics capabilities to resolve key university challenges Our Culture Our Values inspire us, wherever we are in the world, and guide how we live and work together. We are fundamentally transforming the world of research at RMIT, from providing industry leading opportunities for researchers to introducing world-first technology. We’re proud to be reshaping our processes and capabilities – and in doing so, we’re becoming a trusted partner in creating the future of research. What unites us is our purpose and our values; they are at the heart of who we are, what we stand for, how we make decisions and connect with each other. Our people make everything at the University possible. We encourage new approaches to work and learning, stimulating change to drive positive impact. RMIT exists to create transformative experiences for our students, getting them ready for life and work. You will be a part of a productive and collaborative team, who values working relationships and outcomes through open and inclusive planning, continuous information sharing and transparent work practices. When you join our team, you'll be able to access a range of benefits. From travel to fitness, there's something for everyone. About The Role RMIT is embarking on an ambitious agenda with implementation of the Data & Analytics Strategy to enable its business strategy to 2025. This position will play a critical role across RMIT in ensuring the enterprise data is managed, governed and implemented in accordance to best industry practice. You will oversee the implementation of data management standards and guidelines in line with RMIT Data & Analytics Strategy, provide direction to IT and Portfolios on the key principles, regulations and rules for managing data as an asset. You will also support the leadership and delivery of RMIT-wide and Portfolio initiatives, providing consulting and strategic input at concept/planning stage and providing leadership to ensure that data is managed as a strategic resource. About You You will be an experienced data architecture leader who has worked with enterprise data platforms (Data Warehousing, ETL, Data Governance and Quality, Analytics or BI). Ideally, you will have practical experience in one or more of: BI and Analytics, Data Architecture, Data Engineering, preferably in the context of a significant program of work such as a data analytics program or a transformation program. In addition, you will have experience in managing conceptual and logical data models and have experience in architectures for cloud based data and analytics platforms. Demonstrated ability to influence and advise senior stakeholders across a variety of scenarios will be imperative to your success in this role. Bring your whole self to work: We are better for our diversity. When we listen to those who are different to us, or challenge us, we grow stronger together. When we feel like we belong, we can achieve so much more. We respect each other, embrace our differences and build a sense of belonging in our team and beyond. We’re proud to share with you some of our wins: RMIT University is an Athena SWAN member and the College of Science, Engineering and Health is central to driving improvements in gender equality, diversity and inclusion, particularly in the Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics and Medicine (STEMM) disciplines. RMIT was placed 10th in the 2019 Randstad Employer Brand Research Awards, up five spots from 2018.We were named as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency in 2019.We achieved Gold Employer status for LGBTIQ inclusion in the Australian Workplace Equality Index (AWEI) in 2018 and now in 2019.We were recognised as a top five employer in 2018 for workplace accessibility with the Australian Network on Disability.Exceeding our targets in our Reconciliation Action Plan for Bundyi Girri – an important step in our reconciliation journey. To Apply If this sounds like you, we would love to hear from you. To find out more, please see the position description below.  Position Description - Lead Data Architect.pdf Alternatively, if you would like to discuss further please reach out to Daniela Amato, Talent Acquisition Advisor on 03 9925 0375. Applications close on Sunday 27th October 2019 at 11:55 pm.  RMIT is an equal opportunity employer committed to being a child safe organisation. We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community. Description: About Us The Endeavour Drinks Group ambition is bold, we want to be the world's best drinks retailer. We know that expectations of retail have never been higher so our transactions must be instant, and our services must be intuitive and personal. We are embarking on our next generation of growth, and we want you to be an influential part of it. Our family of leading brands is well respected and highly visible throughout Australia, New Zealand and the world; from Dan Murphy’s, our market leading destination drinks merchant, to our local convenience offering at BWS, and our Cellarmasterwines and Langtons businesses  with each of them commanding a leadership position in their respective category. The Role As a Data Scientist you will support the Endeavour Drinks Group to develop, implement and optimise analytical and predictive models to deliver better product & customer data increasing the effectiveness Customer campaigns. You will create and manage the pipeline of work to ensure delivery within timeframes & ensure effective adoption of data science models and outputs. You will champion Data Science helping to demonstrate the understanding of the benefits of data science to drive improved business outcomes. Key responsibilities in this role will also include: Work closely with key stakeholders to understand business questions and execute data science projects that deliver business solutions Work with our data engineering and technology teams to identify the right big data infrastructure to support our future ambitions Design, build & maintain a feature set from our customer, product and transactional data which can be utilised to build machine learning algorithms. Develop and maintain state of the art advanced statistical and machine learning models (GLM, Random Forests, GBM, xGBoost, etc) to drive Woolworths Rewards marketing strategies and tactical executions. Responsible for the end-to-end data science execution including scoping, building, testing, implementation, maintenance, tracking and optimisation of predictive models.  Develop, maintain and enhance variety of customer segmentation models to uncover customer insights. Interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially focussed recommendations to support business decisions. A little about you Key to your success in this role is your proven experience in data science, data analytics and data exploration, a real advocate and champion across all data management activities. Technically you will be sound with end-to-end data science execution including scoping, building, testing, implementation, maintenance, tracking and optimisation of predictive models. You will be detailed and process-orientated by nature, with the ability to provide insightful analysis and pragmatic advice in a rapidly changing environment. You are able to effectively communicate and tell a story through your insights with a natural ability to influence key stakeholders in a complex organisation.  To be successful in this role, you will likely possess the following: 3-5 years experience developing predictive models in commercial environments, preferably exposure to merchandising and Marketing.  Ideally experience in retail vertical markets (not essential) Experience in developing class-leading algorithms to drive commercial outcomes. Advanced working knowledge of analytical programming: SQL, SAS, R or Python. Exposure to Big Data platforms, such as Data bricks or Spark Experience with SQL essential; exposure to Azure or GCP preferred. Experience in working in complex, multi-stakeholder environments.  Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organise, analyse and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy. Tertiary qualified in relevant discipline (Statistics, Data Science, Mathematics, Computer Science).Prior experience in a commercial/business support or data/insights analyst role coupled with relevant tertiary qualifications. What's in it for you An attractive remuneration package Opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest and best minds in Australia Training and Education - We pride ourselves in helping you realise your potential and give you the opportunity to be innovative An exciting career - as our business grows, so do the opportunities for our Team Members If you meet a number of requirements (and not all), we encourage you to submit your application. As an inclusive, team-first company, our people are at the core of everything we do. As our Group continues to evolve, innovate and support our communities, we encourage our team members to do the same with their own careers, by providing ongoing opportunities to grow and make a real difference.  We value diversity and aim to create a vibrant and inclusive workforce which reflects the communities we serve.  Sound like your next opportunity? An Australia household name is looking for a Principal Data Scientist to lead and manage exciting and innovative Data Science projects An Australia household name is looking for a Principal Data Scientist to lead and manage exciting and innovative Data Science projects here in Melbourne.This organisation has one of the largest databases in Australia and you will:  work with one the most talented and passionate Data science teams in Australia have influence and a direct impact on the strategic direction of the organisation have the chance to be part of cutting edge modelling projects utilising hundreds of data assets.   Uniquely for a Data Science position this is less of a “hands on” role so we are looking for someone who has the technical background but is looking to move into a more strategic and delivery focused role.  As the Principal Data Scientist, you will be considered a senior member to the Data community. You will act as the key link to the business and the Data Science team and help ensure the end to end development of the Data Science solution is delivered effectively.  Key responsibilities include:  Leading and driving the successful delivery of Data Science projects end to end Creating and managing teams, in some cases beyond Data Scientists, to ensure the projects are accomplished. Act as a thought leader on Data Science and advance modelling techniques Work with Data Science teams and guide on best fit techniques and tools for various tasks Build effective relationships across various data teams and the wider business and senior leadership team Project management, defining business and technical requirements, resource planning and analytic solution design and innovation in a big data environment, as well quality control of analytical output.  The successful candidate will have some of these key skills:  Experience as a Data Scientist that has led projects end to end A technical background in Analytics, delivering insights and knowledge of Data Science tools such as Python, R, Big Data, Cloud Knowledge of stakeholder and project management skills A passion for engaging and telling the story with Data   The last point of passion is something we are really looking for. This is an exciting and different type of role that offers an incredibly strategic and fascinating perspective on how data science is delivered within a commercial setting. The growth of this area is substantial and this role is seen as a key figure that will be able to progress quickly within this organisation.  For more info please contact Stuart Garland on 0434 984 195

The Toll Group is the Asian region's leading provider of integrated logistics services, generating annual revenue of AU$8.3 billion and employing over 40,000 people across an extensive network of 1,200 sites throughout more than 50 countries across the world. This role is also responsible for ensuring consistency, conciseness and effective coordination in the delivery of executive briefings on emerging and realised security incidents. Extensive experience in presenting and communication of data protection, risk and compliance material. Extensive experience in regulatory compliance such as PCI-DSS, GDPR, SOC, SOX, JSOX etc. Ability to articulate a Risk or Data Protection position to technical to executive forums Risk and Data Protection experience across the Cyber domain Understanding of Cyber Security Control Frameworks such as NIST, ISM/PSPF, ISO, CIS, SANS, ASD Communication, Stakeholder Management, Planning, Process & Accountability IT Security Industry Certification, e.g. MCSE, CISSP, CISM, SANS, CompTIA  In return, you will be rewarded with an inclusive and dynamic team environment, a passionate company culture and the opportunity to be an integral part of Toll’s new direction.
