Experience working on developer tools such as Jupyter, pycharm, Git etc.* Experience in distributed data processing in at least of these: EMR, Dataflow, Dataproc, Cloudera Spark etc.* Experience in building SQL and NoSQL data warehouses in at least one of these: Hive/HBase/Redshift/Azure data warehouse/BigQuery.* Experience with cloud based big data stack from one of the leading public cloud based provider such as GCP, AWS or Azure.* Understanding  of Data Engineering and Data Management practices in cloud.* Experience in building various frameworks for Data quality and validation checks in Data Ingestion, Data Processing, Data Warehousing for enterprise data lake.* Big Data Engineering certification is desirable but not imperative.* Understanding of DevOps, Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery principles to build automated pipelines for deployment and production assurance on the data platform.* Knowledge of building self-contained applications using Docker and Kubernatives.* Ability to articulate/relate complex technology material to a variety of different types of stakeholders.* Excellent social and communication skills, with a passion for mentoring and knowledge sharing.* Experienced in Agile / Scrum projects. Job_Title: Research Fellow / Fellow | Data Assimilation Analyst | Institute for Water futures
Description: Classification: Level B Classification: Academic Level B or Level CSalary package: $99,809 - $133,202 per annum plus 17% superannuationTerm: Tenure Track (Level B) or Continuing (Level C) Institute overview:The Australian National University (ANU) made a major and on-going investment in water research through its National Institute Grant to establish the Institute for Water Futures (IWF). The IWF brings together researchers in 10 water-related positions from across sciences, social sciences, humanities and public policy within the ANU and has established research partnerships with state and federal water agencies, and other research organisations. The IWF mission is to support sustainable water futures and to identify transformative, innovative and robust strategies to resolve the water challenges of today and tomorrow. The IWF is seeking to recruit several highly motivated and capable early career water researchers from multiple disciplines and areas of expertise. The successful candidates will be expected to work in collaboration with ANU colleagues, research partners including Bureau of Meteorology, CSIRO, Geoscience Australia, Murray Darling Basin Authority, NSW Department of Industry Queensland Water Modelling Network, Atlas of living Australia and communities to effectively respond to real-world water challenges facing Australia and the Asia and Pacific regions.  Working for the IWF , the successful candidates will be actively collaborating with key stakeholders and researchers as part of an inter-disciplinary water research team and will be effectively contributing to the research and teaching program at the IWF. Position overview:The IWF and the Research School of Earth Sciences seek an outstanding advanced early- or mid-career researcher with a demonstrable track record of incorporating observational data into numerical models that represent and track the transport of water in the Earth system. The successful candidate will engage in research and teaching, and have a strong background in data inversion and/or data assimilation (e.g. Kalman filtering), along with interest in, and a general understanding of, how ecosystems and other aspects of the climate system interact with the hydrosphere. There will be a future need to adapt existing models and practices to exploit new remote sensing data, as future missions become operational (e.g. SWOT). Our ideal candidate will work closely with other geodesists and hydrologists in the IWF to develop efficient processes for assimilating remotely sensed estimates of total water storage, soil moisture and surface water levels, and be keen to contribute to the broader, interdisciplinary goals. For further information about these roles, please contact Associate Professor Paul Tregoning, E: [email protected] To find out more about the Institute for Water Futures, please follow visit our site: https://fennerschool.anu.edu.au/research/affiliated-research-groups/institute-water-futures-iwf We welcome and develop applicants from diverse backgrounds, experiences and ideas and encourage applications from individuals who may have had non-traditional career paths, who may have taken a career break or who have achieved excellence in careers outside of academia. ANU Values diversity and inclusion and is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to those of all backgrounds and identities. People with a disability are encouraged to apply. For more information about staff equity at ANU, read here: https://services.anu.edu.au/business-units/human-resources-division/equity-and-diversity The Australian National University is a world-leading institution and provides a range of lifestyle, financial and non-financial rewards and programs to support staff in maintaining a healthy work/life balance whilst encouraging success in reaching their full career potential. Description: At Hasbro, we embrace the unique skills, experiences, talents and perspectives of our global workforce which, combined with our culture of curiosity and innovation, generates the best ideas. We live our values of Community, Passion, Integrity and Creativity, and we’re committed to giving our 5,000+ employees opportunities to build their individual capabilities, balance work and life, deliver excellence through team work and thrive personally. This enables us to deliver results in all aspects of our business. We're seeking a Design & Development Analyst to join our Global Development Team.  The Development Analyst is a hybrid role that utilizes the technical skills of an analyst and couples it with product development knowledge. Through the understanding of  the development process, terms, decision-making events, in conjunction with scripting, data aggregation, application development and report-building, this role supports the needs of the Global Development Organization. A Day in the Life of a Development Analyst:  You will support an existing array of internally developed product development applications. Ensure data are being transferred correctly from source systems like PTC Windchill Flex, Global Milestone System, Cost Workbook, Tooling Tracker and SAP. Maintain system documentation and data dictionary.  You will co-author, design and implement new development applications and reports. Requires basic knowledge of development processes, data sources and all aspects of new product launch. Also responsible for developing in the most visually efficient way possible.  You will partner with Product Development, GBT, Operations and IT to on-board new data sources and develop appropriate connections between unconnected data sources and establish tables, views and stored procedures as required within Development Intelligence data warehouse.  You will conduct analysis on Hasbro internal data sources to support Product Development objectives. Leverage product development, marketing launch and supply chain knowledge to provide insights to Sr Leadership to manage GDO and or provide information to make real time and accurate decisions based on the conversion of data into information.  You will manage assigned Development Intelligence projects. This may require any or all of interviewing, collaborating and or training of a diverse group across many locations. Such as Project Management, Cost Engineering, Finance, GBT, Operations in multiple locations globally including RI, LA, Canada and Hong Kong.  You are a problem solver who will continually explore reporting tools, development languages and application to help Product Development meet its goals.   What you’ll bring:   You will bring prior experience in the following areas: data mining, data analysis, report building or product development knowledge. B.S. in a quantitative field (e.g., comp sci, engineering, economics) or equivalent work experience. Strong Excel capabilities, including topics like lookups, PowerQuery, PivotTables, VBA, application macros and automation. Experience with a data exploration tool such as Tableu or PowerBI a plus. Entry level data and SQL skills, abililty to design and optimize queries and build data structures. Join multiple data sources, advanced stored procedures and job scheduling, transmission to and from databases, ETL and data warehousing.  Entry level skills in a major data-related scripting language and meaningful libraries such as R, Python, Flask, Pandas, Numpy. Entry level experience with front-end and back-end web development technologies: servers HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, Ajax, Bootstrap, jQuery, d3js. Experience with file version control (git) or similar preferred. Excellent written and verbal interpersonal skills – experience working with business partners and senior leaders on a regular basis.  Proven project management capabilities, able to oversee multiple projects and prioritize a variety of incoming requests. Strong collaborative skills and ability to partner among peers in an open work space critical.   Hasbro is committed to equality of opportunity in all aspects of employment. We are committed to making all employment decisions without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, national origin, age, marital status, or any other legally protected status.

Duties The Destroyer System Program Office (DDGSPO) has been established to sustain the Air Warfare Destroyer (AWD) at Garden Island, Sydney. The Technical Data Manager (TDM) will work for the Configuration Manager and the Integrated Data Environment (IDE) Team Leader to ensure that the needs of technical data management are represented in the greater IDE. The TDM will ensure that technical data provides assurance of technical integrity and seaworthiness and informs asset management and other DDGSPO business decisions. The Technical Data Manager will be responsible for the management of DDGSPO technical data. They will be responsible for planning, directing, controlling and coordinating the identification, acquisition, analysis, storage, use and disposal of the technical data required to maintain the technical integrity of DDGSPO materiel through-life. • Responsibilities will also include:• development and maintenance of the Technical Data Management Plan;• integrity and configuration management of technical data;• facilitating the identification and procurement of new technical data requirements;• managing technical data access, security, intellectual property and export control;• distribution of incoming data to appropriate engineers and technicians;• storage and disposal of technical data; and• reviews and internal audits of the Technical Data Management System. The TDM will manage the transition of technical data, from acquisition to sustainment and then over the life of the assets and their support systems. They will be required to obtain a working knowledge of the Naval Logistic Information Systems, centered on the Configuration Management Tool, the Asset Management Planning System, and the Military Integrated Logistic Information System. A background in technical data management, from either an IT or end-user perspective, is preferred as an understanding of both is paramount to the successful conduct of this role. Please note Baseline clearance is required to be obtained initially, with the expectation that this will be upgraded to NV1 once engagement has commenced. Description: Seeing Machines is a world leader in human machine interaction. We are seeking a Data Acquisition Specialist to join our team and help us meet the ultimate challenge of understanding human beings. Seeing Machines designs human sensing technology (Driver Monitoring Systems) which focuses on real-world, human driving behaviours to make the world a safer, smarter place for drivers, operators and the wider community.Our Data & Validation Group is vital to our success. This team collects and manages large validation and algorithm training datasets and applies their statistical analysis expertise to algorithm validation. They are an internal service division and provide vital assistance to the Research & Development team and other engineering groups.About the opportunityThe Seeing Machines Data Acquisition team works alongside key business units, marking up video datasets and preparing the data for machine learning algorithm validation and training. As a Data Acquisition Specialist, you will:  * gather data collection requirements through consultation with algorithm scientists and algorithm performance engineers* develop data collection protocols by soliciting and sharing technical feedback from all relevant stakeholders* prepare, execute and supervise data collection, data annotation and dataset curation activities in accordance with the approved data collection protocols and relevant guidelines* monitor progress against milestones and administer review processes to ensure quality benchmarks are met* support the Data Acquisition Supervisor by providing performance feedback on data acquisition assistants, and promote a continuous learning culture within the team About youAs a Data Acquisition Specialist, you will provide critical support to the R&D team - as they apply machine learning technology to continued development of our class leading algorithms and technology.We are seeking people with the following attributes:  * strong organisational and management skills, with an ability to operate in a rapidly changing environment whilst maintaining high work quality and attention to detail* good communication and interpersonal skills, and the ability to hold effective technical discussions with engineers* ability to work with incomplete technical information and possess good problem-solving, analytical and critical thinking skills* experience in writing technical documents and reports* strong computer literacy, and experience with Microsoft Office* experience in developing scripts (e.g. in Python) to process data* experience in a technical supervisory role, especially in video image data collecting, processing and annotation (labeling) is highly desirable.* a current driver's license and confidence to drive on public roads in order to assist in data collection activities. How to apply To apply, please upload your current resume and cover letter outlining your interest in the role and how you could make a difference at Seeing Machines. About us Seeing Machines is a world leader in driver-machine interaction. We harness human factors science to create artificial intelligence (AI) technology that observes the driver's attention – reliably, unobtrusively, and in real time – and intervenes seamlessly when necessary. Specialised computer vision algorithms underpin Seeing Machines' core camera-based driver monitoring technology. Algorithms allow us to precisely track eye gaze, head position and pupil size while our state-of-the-art AI technology analyses the data to quickly and accurately detect driver drowsiness, distraction and microsleep levels. We work with some of the world's leading brands to deliver this technology, helping keep drivers and operators engaged across commercial transport and logistics, automotive, aviation, rail and mining industries. The WHY of our technology • According to the World Health Organisation, over 1.3 million people die in road accidents, globally. • The American Automobile Association says that 1 in every 10 auto accidents in the US is fatigue related and that 25% of US car accidents are caused by distraction. • European Commission recommends that camera-based driver monitoring technology be mandated to enhance safety in cars, vans, trucks and buses from 2022. • Air traffic is set to double over 15 years and the world's aviation fleet is set to double in 20 years. This creates a huge demand for more pilots and air traffic management which increases pressure on training and safety frameworks for the aviation industry, globally. • Seeing Machines' Guardian technology for commercial fleets has been scientifically proven to reduce fatigue related driver events by more than 90%.

Let's talk about the role and responsibilities: The Scrum Master is a servant leader of the project squad, who promotes and manages the agile methodology within squads. The Scrum Master should encourage self-organisation of the Scrum Team and allow them to make their own decisions with a focus on continuous improvement. They are responsible for facilitating agile ceremonies when required including daily stand-ups, short and long-term planning, estimation sessions and sprint retros. Scrum Masters are also expected to coordinate dependencies with other teams, establish and implement process frameworks and lead process improvement activities. Work with the Feature Lead to facilitate the day-to-day efficient operation of the squad and velocity, and develop and maintain clear communication and stakeholder management.The responsibilties, skills and duties of the scrum master will include:   * Delivery planning with feature lead and team to make estimations;* Maintain JIRA Hygiene, and prioritise and assign tasks to team member;* Promote Agile way of working amongst team members;* Manage changes and deployment into production;* Ensure team is working at capacity;* Manage team members that are part of the client organization;* Develop and maintain communication and stakeholder management;* Help drive analysis and engagements with stakeholders;* Utilize individual strengths within the squad and ensuring that squad members work collaboratively to accomplish common goals;* Ensure that the squad heads in the right direction from a technical standpoint;* Maintaining cross-functionality in the squad;* Oversee all incoming and outgoing project documentation;* Manage releases and technical escalations with the feature team lead;* Clear obstacles and impediments blocking the team and protect the team from external interruptions and distractions; Passionate people are Capgemini's Ace of spades. We believe that every one of us is an architect of positive futures. Not only will you work alongside inspiring colleagues with a world of experience, but you'll also have access to great benefits including, salary continuance insurance, paid parental leave, education assistance, salary packaging, the ability to purchase additional leave; as well as discounts on entertainment, financial and wellbeing services, travel and shopping. Talk to us about working part-time or full time. Ranked among Ethisphere's 2019 Most Ethical Companies in the World (for the 7th year running!), our seven values are at the heart of everything we do - Honesty, Boldness, Trust, Team Spirit, Freedom, Fun and Modesty. As Social Innovators, we are committed to making a positive impact on the planet and our communities. Description: Exciting opportunity for a professional to work within our data collection & analysis team.  Work in VIC/ NSW or QLD office. About UsWe’ve been doing it since 1960! The Australian Road Research Board (ARRB) is the source of independent expert transport knowledge, with almost 60 years of experience focused on delivering a connected and adaptable future for Australia and New Zealand. ARRB has a strong heritage supporting and delivering high quality applied research for Australian and New Zealand state road agencies (our Members) and for the community. Our teams are made up of world-leading roads, transport and infrastructure professionals who analyse and interpret global research and apply it to the Australian and New Zealand context. Our Mission: Creating knowledge for tomorrow’s transport challenges and solutions for today.Our Values: Integrity Transformative, Collaborative and Energy and PassionOur Vision: To help make the world’s cities smarter, cleaner, greener, safer, more efficient and productive through intelligent transport solutions. Why join ARRB:ARRB is a dynamic and vibrant organisation providing exciting opportunities for people to do great things, to tackle the big infrastructure questions, and to see these solutions being practically applied. Our staff operate within a state-of-the-art workplace with multi-disciplinary teams with highly evolved skills. At ARRB, the National Transport Research Organisation, innovation, personal and professional development is fostered and nurtured - enabling true collaboration. About the role and you:Work within a team that offers quality data collection for large-scale network surveys, local road system surveys and/or ride quality testing with various configurations to meet client’s requirements. Our Data Collection and Analysis Team is seeking a highly motivated Data Analyst/ Technical Officer who will focus their efforts on the timely and accurate processing and analysis of road asset and condition data to join either our Melbourne, Sydney or Brisbane based team. We are seeking individuals who are keen to be a part of ARRB’s future and who will be a key team member, to contribute to the delivery of local, State and National projects and initiatives. In this position you will:   Focus on data processing and analysis including quality assurance checking Conduct basic analysis of condition data for input into Asset Management projects Process condition and strength data into formats as required by clients Be part of a pivotal team providing prompt, high quality delivery results to clients Contribute to the on time and on budget delivery of projects   We seek an individual who has:   An appropriate qualification (in data science/engineering) or more than two years recent/relevant work experience in SQL server environments, data analysis and database management Advanced level of computer packages, particularly in MS Excel and MS Access Familiarity with working in the Windows environment Well-developed analytical and technical skills GIS skills A tolerant, flexible and easy-going nature   What we offer: An exciting, dynamic and collaborative workplace with challenging roles, where your skills, knowledge and experience will be recognised and respected, including:   Opportunities to contribute to high-profile and interesting projects Opportunities to contribute to high-profile and interesting projects which make a difference to the community. The change to work collaboratively on local and national projects with a network of experts and colleagues around the country. Healthy work-life balance, with flexible arrangements for accruing time off Strong support for career development and further study A competitive salary & staff benefits Access to paid parental leave Potential salary packaging benefits available Additional leave days over end-of-year holiday period   To be considered:   Applicants must be Australian Citizens / Permanent Residents Press the "APPLY" button in this job advertisement to apply. Please ensure you attached your CV, Cover Letter (addressing selection criteria) and answer the screening questions provided. Description: Temporary full-time appointment for a period up to 17 November 2021 Location: 105 Phillip St, Parramatta About the Department of Education We ensure young children get the best start in life by supporting and regulating the early childhood education and care sector. We are the largest provider of public education in Australia with responsibility for delivering high-quality public education to two-thirds of the NSW student population. For more information about the Department of Education, please visit NSW Department of Education About the directorate The Centre for Education Statistics and Evaluation (CESE), undertakes in-depth analysis of education programs and outcomes across early childhood, school, training and higher education to inform whole-of-government, evidence based decision-making. Put simply, it seeks to find out what works best. CESE’s three main responsibilities are to: provide data analysis, information and evaluation that improve effectiveness, efficiency and accountability of education programs and strategies. collect essential education data and provide a one-stop shop for information needs – a single access point to education data that has appropriate safeguards to protect data confidentiality and integrity build capacity across the whole education sector so that everyone can make better use of data and evidence. ideally Tableau, Qlik, PowerBI and/or Oracle Analytics Cloud Strong experience in translating high level requirements and designs into deliverables Strong experience in a large scale, complex system integration projects in a cross domain, cross-partner, multi-application, multi-sourced technology environment Experience working in Agile (SAFe) frameworks   Nice to Have  Strong interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills Highly developed conceptual, analytical, problem solving skills and systems and process thinking Ability to work under pressure Ability to work on current initiatives and prioritise and balance work accordingly At least 3 solid years of hands on experience modern languages: Python, J2EE, C# ,JSON, XML, XSD, Scala At least 3 solid years of hands on experience developing and enhancing ETL jobs At least 3 solid years of hands on experience designing data warehouse and/or data models At least 3 years’ experience working in cloud data storage mechanisms (e.g. S3) Excellent working knowledge of database data dictionary objects (any DB) Familiarity with version control systems (Mercurial, Git, Perforce, Subversion) Experience loading data from web services / cloud services / S3 Familiarity with BI/DW industry best practices Familiarity with automated deployment methods & tools Experience with dimensional data modelling principles (e.g. star and snowflake schemas, denormalised data structures) Eager to learn new domains such as Machine Learning Pragmatic, concrete approach to software delivery  Australia is a great place, we know that! Job_Title: Team Leader, Data Management (Ongoing Full Time)
Description: RFS Level 10/11 Ongoing full time role - 35 hour work week Location: Sydney Olympic Park Vacancy Reference: 19/70 About the NSW Rural Fire Service The NSW Rural Fire Service (NSW RFS) is the lead combat agency for bush fires in NSW. Working closely with other agencies we respond to a range of emergencies including structure fires, motor vehicle accidents and storms that occur within rural fire districts.  Our vision and mission is to provide a world standard of excellence in the provision of a community-based fire and emergency service. To protect the community and our environment we will minimise the impact of fire and other emergencies by providing the highest standards of training, community education, prevention and operational capability.   Our corporate video and Our Plan provides further insight into the NSW Rural Fire Service. About the role We’re looking for a senior data manager with team leadership capability to oversee the management and maintenance of enterprise spatial systems, operational database and cloud data warehousing within the NSW RFS. Your position will engage strategically with ICT Management and the Enterprise Architecture team to determine the future technological directions of the RFS data management landscape, contributing to critical projects such as the Automatic Vehicle Location, Resource Management, Common Operating Picture and Incident Management systems. The role supports initiatives of the NSW RFS, following the objectives of the ICT strategy, NSW Government Policy and best practices within industry. About you Your leadership skills are evident in your continual learning, both formal and informal and your ability to share your knowledge with others. Your focus on the customer leads you to continually improve upon organisational process and technologies to offer a better experience to the end user and prompt resolution to complex support issues. You expect a high level of personal motivation from your team and lead by example. You are passionate about the value spatial data can provide to emergency service organisations and promote best practice development to encourage wide ranging use of the tools and technologies across the organisation. Experience building and managing AWS Cloud Data Warehousing solutions and DMBoK2 Certified Data Management Professional Practitioner level or equivalent would be highly desirable. Effective information management and application integration strategies are your bread and butter and you are energised by the opportunity to bring legacy data into an AWS warehouse solution to enable the organisation to utilise analytics and AI tools for the future needs of the organisation. For further information about the role, please click here to view the role description. Please address the essential criteria in your cover letter. To be successful in this role, you must meet the following essential requirements:  - An Advanced Diploma or Degree in a relevant discipline, or equivalent expertise.  - ESRI ArcGIS Enterprise Geodata Management Professional certification or equivalent expertise.  - Required to participate on an afterhours and/or on call roster. - During periods of major fire activity, the incumbent may be required to support operational management activities consistent with their skills and background. We offer: - Flexible working arrangements - Attractive salary and superannuation - Attractive leave entitlements - Working for a highly regarded emergency service, where supporting the local community is at the forefront of our business strategy - Opportunities for professional development  - A brand new building in a location close to public transport - 35 hours per week For further information, please review the role description or contact Natalie Hill on 0419 609 574. Applications close: Sunday 27 October 2019, 11:59 pm Applying for the role:  To apply for this role, you will need to submit an online application via http://iworkfor.nsw.gov.au/ and include:- A cover letter (maximum one A4 page). - A resume, which clearly details skills, experience and capabilities required for this role as per the role description. This should include two referees, one of which is a current or recent supervisor, and their contact details (maximum 5 pages). Click here for further information on applying for a role in the public sector. Job Notes: - Prior to applying for this role candidates should download the Role Description. Candidates must demonstrate in their application how they meet the focus capabilities and other essential requirements. - The NSW Rural Fire Service is committed to creating a diverse, inclusive and flexible workforce which reflects the community we serve. We welcome and encourage applications from all ages and genders, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, culturally and linguistically diverse groups, the LGBTIQ+ community, veterans, refugees and those with a disability. - Relevant criminal history, referee checks and prior employment checks will be conducted on recommended applicants. - A talent pool may be established for future temporary and ongoing roles with similar focus capabilities. The talent pool may be available to hiring managers across the state over a 18 month period. Relevant Information: NSW Public Sector Capability Framework NSW RFS Code of Conduct and Ethics

Description: •    Permanent role•    Advertising closes 19th November Due to growth and a focus on personalisation, we’re currently looking for a passionate and experienced analyst who loves data and loves travel who is seeking to develop their career in next generation data technologies.  Jetstar is looking to expand on its analytics capability to prioritise and drive economic return from its investment in understanding audiences and behaviour on our digital properties.  Working as part of a team, you’ll work alongside our marketing, digital, data science and product management teams to play a crucial role in analysing and deriving value from customer data. You will be responsible for leading the scoping and delivery of analytics projects using a hypothesis-driven approach and focusing on the highest value impact. As well as interpreting complex information and developing insights/recommendations for presentation and key decision making.  Tools such as Adobe Analytics, SQL and Power BI will be utilised in this role to interrogate and data mine various data sources to extract customer intelligence. In addition, this role involves educating end-users on the insights which have been developed and advising how they can be utilised to drive value to the business. What you’ll do:•    Develop insights and recommendations to drive audience segmentation, activation & conversion rate optimisation•    Apply expertise in analysis, data visualisation and data-mining to tell the story behind the numbers•    Present insights, findings and recommendations across customer journeys and channels•    Empower our teams to utilise and realise value from real time data•    Validate audiences in terms of data availability & timeliness, audience size and benefits•    Develop models using various statistical methodologies•    Create test & learn scenarios for performance validation•    Develop multiple dashboards that increase efficiencies in reporting requirements. What you need: •    Extensive experience in extracting and manipulating large volume data with SQL and other programming languages (ie. Python or R)•    Experience in data focused marketing automation & personalisation including experience with in cloud-based data solutions, Adobe Analytics, Oracle Marketing Cloud•    Exposure to Amazon Web Services infrastructure preferred•    Experience with data visualisation tools such as PowerBI preferred or Tableau•    Experience with user research techniques desired•    Experience in customer based analytics desired•    Passionate about troubleshooting with a great attention to detail•    You have a university degree in business, statistics or a related field•    A background in the airline industry is not necessary, but a strong interest in the industry and a desire to learn more would be highly desirable. About Us The Jetstar Group has airlines in Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Japan and Vietnam. Since launch in 2004, we have grown from a team of 700 to 7,600 and have flown more than 250 million passengers. Collectively we now offer more than 5000 flights a week to more than 85 destinations in 17 countries and territories across the Asia Pacific region, with a fleet of more than 130 aircraft.  Our CultureJetstar is alive with a sense of adventure. Day in and day out, our teams search for new places to fly, new ways to add value and new ideas to improve performance. If you love the road less travelled, you’ll love working here because ours is a team who innovate every day, thrive on delivery, support each other and celebrate our successes. You’ll be supported to challenge, anticipate and explore while you work will connect people and enrich lives. We encourage diversity and aim to create an environment where our employees feel valued, respected and enabled. Our BenefitsTeam members have access to heavily discounted fares to destinations all over the world – not only for team members, but for their favourite travel companions too. Our staff travel benefit includes discounts on airfares, accommodation, car hire and travel insurance for both domestic and international travel. Discounts can be used within the Jetstar Group airlines, Qantas and other partner airlines.

Description: About the University of Melbourne The University of Melbourne is consistently ranked among the leading universities in the world, holding the number 1 spot in Australia and number 32 among all universities globally (Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2019). We are globally engaged, renowned for delivering learning & teaching programs, we are deeply connected to business, government and the community through our research and impact, all to achieve and contribute to a better society which helps transform our lives. About the Petascale Campus Initiative https://mdap.unimelb.edu.au/ The University invests in state-of-the-art research infrastructure to enable excellent researchers to drive quality and innovation. As part of this investment, the Petascale Campus Initiative (PCI) is a five-year plan to increase the informatics, data and compute capabilities for the University over 2018 to 2022 The PCI involves a significant new investment in computing infrastructure and the workforce required to enable access and use of such infrastructure. Recruitment of the workforce began mid 2019, and as a result the Melbourne Data Analytics Platform (MDAP) has been formed. This team is working to ensure our researchers, students and collaborators have the necessary tools and resources now and in the future to keep us at the leading edge of research in this exciting, fast-paced era of data science. We've created a structure to support our researcher-led vision: embedding a process of continual consideration, development and resourcing for both our digital science infrastructure and the academic specialists who will help us maximise our use of that infrastructure. About the role Reporting to the MDAP Lead, you will take input from the platform's Steering and User committees on matters relating to the operations of the Platform. Duties You will have an opportunity to contribute to issues relating to Australia's public hospitals by using a range of data modelling and analysis methods. This role requires someone who has the ability to work with numbers, interpret large datasets and summarise complex numerical information. Description: Duties The Science to Services Program of the Bureau of Meteorology is seeking a software engineer / data scientist with strong computational science knowledge with a focus on mathematics, statistics or physical sciences to be a key member of an innovative multi-disciplinary team with IT and science specialists which improves weather forecast guidance for operational forecast staff. The focus of this work is on collaborative development, testing and documentation of weather model Ensemble Post Processing (EPP), including machine learning science, software and systems. EPP bias-corrects, combines, downscales and produces weather event probabilities from different state-of-the-art numerical weather prediction guidance. The post-processed guidance supports communication of forecast uncertainty to users, and requires less editing by weather forecasters, allowing for a more efficient high-impact forecast process.  Core competencies include excellent software engineering ability, experience in developing complex scientific applications suitable for operational use, and a good grasp of computational algorithms and application to large data volumes. Machine learning knowledge and experience would be an advantage. Experience and interest in scientific or engineering research and systems development is desirable.  The software used for EPP is written predominantly in C, Python and shell scripts utilising 3rd party scientific and data-handling libraries and is run on high performance Linux platforms. Operation of the applications is time-critical, and will involve work-flow scheduling (using rose-cylc), memory, I/O and parallelism on large high-performance computing systems. Experience in using configuration managers (e.g. rose) will be valued. Modern tools and practices such as git, automated testing and deployment and code reviews are used.  The position will also contribute to EPP science testing (evaluation and visualisation of gridded scientific fields) including through the specification and development of mostly python-based verification libraries, supporting transition to operations. You will collaboratively define, develop and support transition to operations processes, standards and capabilities including testing and deployment capabilities. You will also collaborate with operational staff monitoring quality and execution of operational software, other Science to Services sections, areas of the Bureau managing data services, and others as appropriate. Professional development opportunities relevant to the work will be available. This is a great opportunity to work on meaningful scientific software applications for the public good, in a research environment with a commitment to innovation and quality. Eligibility A degree or diploma from an Australian educational institution, or a comparable overseas qualification, which is appropriate to the duties; OROther comparable qualifications, which are appropriate to the duties. Description: About the University of Melbourne The University of Melbourne is consistently ranked among the leading universities in the world, holding the number 1 spot in Australia and number 32 among all universities globally (Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2019). We are globally engaged, renowned for delivering learning & teaching programs, we are deeply connected to business, government and the community through our research and impact, all to achieve and contribute to a better society which helps transform our lives. About the Petascale Campus Initiative https://mdap.unimelb.edu.au/ The University invests in state-of-the-art research infrastructure to enable excellent researchers to drive quality and innovation. As part of this investment, the Petascale Campus Initiative (PCI) is a five-year plan to increase the informatics, data and compute capabilities for the University over 2018 to 2022 The PCI involves a significant new investment in computing infrastructure and the workforce required to enable access and use of such infrastructure. Recruitment of the workforce began mid 2019, and as a result the Melbourne Data Analytics Platform (MDAP) has been formed. This team is working to ensure our researchers, students and collaborators have the necessary tools and resources now and in the future to keep us at the leading edge of research in this exciting, fast-paced era of data science. We’ve created a structure to support our researcher-led vision: embedding a process of continual consideration, development and resourcing for both our digital science infrastructure and the academic specialists who will help us maximise our use of that infrastructure. About the role Reporting to the MDAP Lead, you will take input from the platform’s Steering and User committees on matters relating to the operations of the Platform. You will be responsible for providing high-level co-ordination and program management; stakeholder engagement; managing day-to-day operations; supporting strategic planning; and documented reporting to stakeholders. In addition, you will initiate and manage a number of key projects to enhance quality, information management and promotion of the Platform. You will also play an integral role in realising the Platform’s vision to put people at the centre of collaborative research, involving computational methodologies. As MDAP is still developing and due to double in size throughout 2020, your ability to establish and maintain collaborative working relationships with key stakeholders will be crucial. About you Postgraduate qualifications or progress towards graduate qualifications and extensive relevant experience; or extensive experience and management expertise; or, and equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training.Demonstrated leadership through coordination and support of research programs.Exemplary skills in project management, strategic operational and business planning and influencing decisions at an executive level with highly developed negotiation skills.Well-developed organisational and time management skills with the capacity to meet deadlines and balance competing demands, to work effectively under pressure and respond to changing priorities and deadlines.Demonstrated ability to foster collaboration and to form and contribute to communities of practice and/or special interest groups.Superior interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills coupled with the capacity to operate effectively as part of a team.High proficiency in a range of computer applications and ability to quickly adapt to new applications.Evidence of commitment to continuous improvement and desire to enact positive change, adapting to new environments and drivers. How to apply To apply for this role, please submit your Cover Letter, CV and responses to the key selection criteria as outlined in the position description. For information to assist you with compiling short statements to answer the selection criteria, please go to: https://about.unimelb.edu.au/careers/selection-criteria MDAP is strongly committed to supporting diversity and flexibility in the workplace. Applications for part-time or other flexible working arrangements will be welcomed and will be fully considered subject to meeting the inherent requirements of the position. Please note to be eligible for this role you must hold valid Australian work rights. Further information on the University's requirements can be found at: https://about.unimelb.edu.au/careers/work-rights Position Description

Description: WHAT WE DO Calibre’s specialist engineering, project and support teams have a proven track record of successfully designing and delivering some of the largest mines and supporting rail infrastructure in Australia. Calibre Group is mobilising a railway System Assurance Team to support delivery of transformational signalling system for a heavy haul iron ore railway operator within the Pilbara region of Western Australia. The new moving block rail system will significantly enhance mine to port throughput, availability and safety. The Project is being delivered by a world leading technology provider who is seeking to leverage local expertise to ensure that system integration, safety and wayside modifications are safe and fit for intended use.  This is a long-term Perth based opportunity that will see you work on an engaging and dynamic project. WHAT YOU’LL DO The primary responsibility of the Safety Engineer (Railway Site Data, Balise & Mobile Work Stations) is to coordinate and perform lifecycle safety assurance associated with CENELEC and activity specific industry standards for communication basedtrain control systems related site data transformation, configuration and design, balise layout design and mobile work stations for possession management. You will be required to perform safety analysis activities on operational scenarios and the impact of configuration data errors on design and safety performance. In this role, you will will develop associated safety cases and SFAIRP arguments in support of design type, testing and commissioning approvals. Assurance activities will include oversight of safety integrity of client processes for design, delivery and functional testing of modification of existing rail operator assets.   WHO YOU ARE You will be familiar with the principles of Data Engineering, System Engineering and Safety Engineering. In particular, familiarity with requirements management and configuration management as applied to safety related data management is required. An understanding of the V-model lifecycle phases as described in ISO/IEC 15288 is required. Knowledge of rail safety standards AS61508 along with the application of the CENELEC group of standards EN 50126, EN 50128, EN 50129 and EN 50159 will be well regarded. WHY CALIBRE? As our most valuable asset, we invest in our employees’ personal and professional growth. We provide a range of benefits, including ongoing professional development, on the job training, study support, leadership and management programs, competitive remuneration packages, generous employee referral incentives and a host of health and wellbeing benefits to help you thrive in our team.   If you want to join the Calibre team APPLY NOW

Group:  Housing and Specialised Services Group Unit:   Housing and Homelessness Collection Operations Unit Classification:  APS Level 5-6 Salary:  $73,824 – $91,534 plus 22% loading in lieu of leave accrual plus superannuation Engagement type:  Contract for 12 months with possibility of extension, full/part-time Location:  Bruce, Canberra ACT Background The Australian Institute of Health and Welfare (AIHW) is an independent corporate Commonwealth entity established by the Australian Government to provide reliable, regular and relevant information and statistics on the health and welfare of Australians. The AIHW has ten groups: Business and Communications; Data Strategies and Integration; Data Governance; Primary Health Care and Veterans; Community Services; Health; Hospitals and Expenditure; Housing and Specialised Services; Indigenous; and Information and Communication Technology Group. We value a positive, friendly, cooperative and productive workplace where people are treated with respect and courtesy, and diverse and unique attributes are recognised and valued. We are committed to providing flexibility in working arrangements to recognise the importance of balancing work commitments with family, caring and other personal commitments outside of work. The AIHW is committed to creating genuine opportunities for all, and welcomes applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people(s), people with a disability and people from diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds. For more information, visit the About Us page of our website. Group Description The Housing and Specialised Services Group develops and reports data to support reporting on the health and welfare of, and provision of services to, a range of vulnerable populations – people with mental illness; people with drug and alcohol addiction; and people experiencing homelessness or needing assistance with housing. Unit Description  The functions of the Housing and Homelessness Collection Operations Unit (HHCOU) include managing the receipt and quality of data for the Specialist Homelessness Services (SHS) collection. The SHS collection obtains information about people, adults and children, who seek assistance from specialist homelessness agencies. Homelessness data for the SHS collection is submitted through a secure AIHW web portal called Validata™. Validata™ accepts and processes data from SHS agencies across the country.  Validata™ performs a number of validation checks on submitted data, which ensures high quality reporting for the collection. Position description We are looking for a talented and enthusiastic APS5-6 Data Analyst with a background in welfare related data. The successful Data Analyst will be part of a small team who will use creative and innovative approaches to interrogate homelessness data to investigate data quality issues, presenting results to a variety of audiences to drive improvements in the quality of the data. A significant part of the work will involve reviewing, developing and testing validation rules in SAS to ensure the quality of the data in the SHS collection. Applicants will have strong verbal and written communication skills and the ability to effectively manage and prioritise their work. Duty Statement Under general direction you will be required to undertake a range of tasks, including: Provide detailed advice and options on a range of professional, technical and administrative mattersLiaise and negotiate with other areas of the AIHW, other government agencies, State and Local authorities, business or community organisationsManipulate datasets to investigate data quality issues in the SHS collectionDevelop and test validation rules in SAS for Validata™Document and identify improvements to business processes within the UnitDevelop and apply new work methods within the area of responsibility Selection criteria Strong conceptual, analytical and research skillsDemonstrated ability to analyse complex data, and create and interpret tabular outputs, using SAS and other softwareWell-developed communication skills, including the ability to synthesise complex information to present data and advice in clear and accessible formats for various audiencesStrong interpersonal skills, with the ability to liaise and negotiate effectively with internal and external stakeholders Additional Information This position will be offered for 12 months, with the possibility of extension. This position will be filled on a contractual basis through a labour hire firm. Applicants must be: willing to undergo a police checkAustralian citizens, or eligible to apply for citizenship, or in the process of obtaining their Australian citizenship How to Apply Applying For further information about this role and how to apply please review the position profile and selection criteria available on our website (https://www.aihw.gov.au/about-us/careers). Applicants must register and apply via the AIHW e-Recruit system on the AIHW website. Your application should include: Closing Date:  11.45pm, Monday 28 October 2019 Contact officer: Stirling Lewis, [email protected], 02 6244 1064

Description: Group: Commodities and Global Markets  Division: Specialised and Asset Finance  Recruiter: Rosemary Coleman If you’re looking to continue to build your career as a Data Analyst, then joining our Specialist Asset Finance Division will see you manage the implementation of our data management strategy, including bringing data under governance and enabling greater use of data for decision making. Specifically you’ll be responsible for the coordination of regulatory data feeds to the Bank’s central data warehouse and investigation of data quality issues. This will include capturing metadata across the Division’s critical data set and embedding best of breed data governance tools as well as the analysis of business processes including assessing data risks and controls in end-to-end data flow. At Macquarie we value the innovation and creativity that diversity of thought brings. The one thing we all have in common is our focus on high performance. The Information Technology (IT) Operations Branch provides the ICT infrastructure services and applications platforms on which DSS corporate and business application services are delivered. The Branch implements ICT infrastructure (network, desktops, telephony, videoconferencing, servers, and storage), and provides IT Service Desk, VIP and 24/7 support for critical business systems and services. Eligibility To be eligible for employment with Department of Social Services (the department), you must be an Australian citizen. An applicant's suitability for employment with the Department will be assessed through a pre-employment screening process. This will include an identity and criminal history background check. The suitable applicant must also obtain and maintain a security clearance conducted by the Australian Government Security Vetting Agency (AGSVA).  Applicants also must be able to establish their background as checkable to be considered eligible for a security clearance. Any gaps or periods of time spent overseas for 12 or more months (cumulative) that cannot be verified by an Australian referee is deemed uncheckable, rendering the applicant ineligible for a security clearance. Background history must cover 5 / 10 years (Baseline / Negative Vet 1 or Negative Vet 2) of employment, education, residential, criminal history and anything else specified by the AGSVA. The Department delivers policies and programs that touch on the lives of almost every Australian. We also manage a significant proportion of the Australian Government Budget and we have responsibility for major Government initiatives like the National Disability Insurance Scheme and the Family Support Program. The diversity of our workforce is very important to us. Job_Title: Senior Research Data Specialist (Health and Medical)
Description: Classification: Senior Manager 1 Classification: Senior Manager 1 (Administration)Salary package: $113,421 - $118,839 per annum plus 17% superannuation Terms: Full time, Continuing (Contingent Funded) Help to design and implement national level programs and services to improve data usage in research;Full time or part time (minimum 25 hours per week);Accommodating working arrangements. Position overview Would you like to make a difference to the way data is used in research?  Do you have a background in health and medical research data? Are you a self-motivated achiever who can pursue opportunities and facilitate national level initiatives? The Senior Research Data Specialist (H&M) is an opportunity to design and implement national level programs to improve the usage of data in research and achieve positive outcomes for society. The Australian Research Data Commons (ARDC) partners with key research system stakeholders to build (at the national level) data assets, information services, analysis and access environments, skills programs, and policy frameworks.  The Senior Research Data Specialist (Health & Medical) will advise ARDC on appropriate directions and opportunities in these areas and will help in the implementation of significant programs of work. This is a “leadership” (rather than “managerial”) role with autonomous responsibility for management of ad hoc teams and initiatives or formal projects and programs. The Senior Research Data Specialist (Health & Medical) in the Australian Research Data Commons (ARDC) has a key role to play in identifying, designing, and implementing projects, programs and services to enhance research by enabling better data management, use, re-use, and sharing. ARDC is one of the Australian Government’s National Collaborative Research Infrastructure (NCRIS) facilities. The ARDC is a transformational initiative that enables Australian research community and industry access to nationally significant, leading edge data intensive eInfrastructure, platforms, skills and collections of high-quality data.  The ARDC seeks to achieve positive health, social, environmental and economic outcomes through the application of contemporary technology and information management to research. Description: We’re on the hunt for a world class Data Analytics Engineer to help us build and ship the data systems that power analytics at Australia’s fastest-growing startup. At Linktree: * Interesting, exciting and challenging work* An agile and autonomous environment* Working at scale with over 3m users globallyThe Linktree story… Linktree is a tool that acts like a content page on the internet, and is transforming the way content is discovered online. The Linktree story starts in 2016, when co-founders Alex, Anthony and Nick were running a digital agency and using Instagram to make announcements about the artists they managed. Created as a side-hustle to solve a simple problem, Linktree has well outgrown its roots, with over 3 million users worldwide, 10,000 new signups every day and over 120 million unique browsers per month. Our audience is broad, spanning publications, artists, celebrities, fashion and beauty influencers, YouTube stars, sports teams and household brands, right the way through to individuals with a side hustle and micro influencers. Linktree users include Alicia Keys, Pharrell, Jamie Oliver, Vice, Expedia, Eva Mendes, Naomi Campbell, World Surf League, Billabong…and many more! To support such unprecedented growth, we’re building powerful new features in Linktree to help our users understand the impact of their content with analytics features. To do that we are expanding our engineering team and are looking for the next generation of Data Analytics experts. As a Data Analytics Engineer, you will be involved in every step of the development process and will enjoy the agile and dynamic startup environment combined with the stability of a well established and fast growing organisation. Join us and do meaningful work alongside global brands! If up for the challenge, you’ll get to: * Build and ship the data systems that power Linktree’s analytics* Work with cross-functional teams of developers, designers, digital producers* Work on broader projects with our parent company, Bolster* Experiment with the projects that range from social listening through to shaping the way the music industry uses data You stand out because you have: * 2+ years commercial data engineering experience* Experience building data pipelines, big data warehouses and shipping features* Ability to lead your own department while working well with dependent teams* Personable, clear and constructive communication skillsTechnical Must Haves : * Experience with Redshift and/or Presto/Athena, Hadoop, Google BigQuery and using them for best practice data architecture* Comfortable working with event stream data from at least one analytics platform like Snowplow, Adobe Analytics or GA360* Experience with ETL scheduling technologies with dependency checking, such as Airflow, as well as schema design and dimensional data modelling* Python (or R) and relevant libraries (e.g. Pandas and NumPy)* Advanced SQL in an analytics environmentBonus Points : * Prior experience with Snowplow* Knowledge of NoSQL, particularly ElasticSearch highly desired* Experience with BI tools like Metabase, Looker, Tableau etc* An interest in music, entertainment, culture and lifestyle industries Linktree in the press: The Australian (https://www.theaustralian.com.au/business/technology/celebrities-at-root-of-linktrees-growth/news-story/6f8f84f56d3c69998a3db626ed855d17)| SmartCompany (https://www.smartcompany.com.au/startupsmart/profiles/linktree-alicia-keys-pearl-jam/) If this sounds inspiring, we’d love to hear from you. This is a full time position based in Collingwood, Victoria.

About Rokt Rokt is the global leader in ecommerce marketing technology. When customers are buying online, they increasingly expect more personalized and relevant experiences. We unlock the hidden potential in every single Transaction Moment.  Born in Sydney, Rokt now operates in the US, Canada, UK, France, Germany, Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, The Netherlands and Japan. We are profitable, growing fast, and having great fun transforming the world of ecommerce.  About You You love tech and research and have a high attention to detail. You like the theory but you also want to see it working in practice. You know what attribution in the marketing world means without looking it up. You like maths, especially algebra and statistics. You build solutions for the long-term, always testing and reviewing your work. In case you don’t know something you are keen and curious to learn. We process large amounts of data to provide insights to the rest of the company and our clients. We are responsible for measuring the uplift (Incrementality) Rokt provides and researching different ways of attribution. We use scrum, doing one week sprints, reviews and retros. About the Role You will be responsible for researching, evaluating, implementing and testing different attribution models such as single/multi-touch, fractional, algorithmic and probabilistic attribution, reading the latest papers on attribution published by Google, Netflix and others. You will develop, maintain and deliver a full range of performance, attribution and risk management analysis, benchmark performance returns against industry standards. You will also collaborate with internal (and sometimes external stakeholders) including product, sales and business analytics teams. Our recruiting process is tough. We hold a high bar because we have a high performing culture - we only want the brightest and the best. Join a community. We believe in in-person, we enjoy each others’ company and we make meaningful connections with each other through global all-staff events, interest groups, sports clubs and social events.  Accelerate your career. Develop through our global training events, ’Level Up’ investment, online training courses and our fantastic people leaders. Take your career to Rokt’speed - average time between promotions is 12 months.  Take a break. When you work hard, we know you also need to rest. We offer generous time off and parental leave policies. Stay happy and healthy. Enjoy catered lunch 3 times a week and healthy snacks in the office, join the gym on us! Become a shareholder. All Rokt’stars have stock options. If we succeed, everyone gets to enjoy the upside.  See the world! Along with our global all-staff events in amazing locations (Phuket, Thailand in January 2020), we also offer generous relocation packages for those interested in moving to another Rokt office. We have cool offices in great cities - London, Tokyo, New York, Singapore, Boston, Sydney.

Job_Title: Research Fellow In Statistical Data Science
Description: The School for Mathematics and Statistics is seeking a qualified and enthusiastic Research Fellow to lead cutting-edge research in statistical approaches in the broad context of Data Science. This includes both theoretical and computational methodological development with the potential for interdisciplinary collaborations. This position offers the ideal candidate a unique opportunity to be part of an exciting and dynamic research program. The successful candidate will be affiliated with the recently launched Data Science at the University of Melbourne (DatUM) initiative partnered between the School of Mathematics and Statistics and School of Computing and Information Systems. The position is housed within the School of Mathematics and Statistics, and will report to Professor Howard Bondell, whose research focuses on a wide variety of methodology and applications. The position offers a rare opportunity to join a growing Data Science initiative, and allows for both a multi-disciplinary environment as well as the development of an individual research agenda. To be considered for this position you will have a PhD or equivalent research higher degree in statistics or related area. You will also have strong computer programming skills in R and a demonstrated aptitude for research. This is a full-time, fixed-term position for 2 years.

Description: Work with one of Australia’s most respected national and independent medical research institutes, making an important contribution on this ground-breaking international cancer research projectGain valuable sector experience in this not-for-profit which offers flexible arrangements, a diverse team and world-leading big data health goalsLocated in Westmead, one of Sydney’s and Australia’s major biomedical research hubs   Children’s Medical Research Institute (CMRI) was Australia’s first dedicated paediatric research facility and is now one of the nation’s most highly regarded independent medical research centres. Our research focuses on the areas of cancer, neuroscience, embryonic development and birth defects, and gene therapy and we have a strong international reputation based on our research outcomes. CMRI’s research programs are supported by state-of-the-art facilities and committed research and support staff. Our achievements are made possible by a loyal network of community supporters, highly engaged donors and the very successful Jeans for Genes® fundraising campaign.The ACRF International Centre for the Proteome of Cancer (ProCan®) is located at CMRI. The ProCan team comprises over 30 staff in proteomics, pathology, software engineering and data science. They use innovative technology to measure thousands of proteins in tiny cancer samples. Led by CMRI's Professor Roger Reddel and Professor Phil Robinson, the ProCan team are analysing tens of thousands of all types of cancers in the 7 year project. Advanced computer analysis techniques are being used to compare the protein data with pathology results and clinical outcome data. ClearScore is one of the leading FinTech companies in the UK. We’re a fast-growing business with a mission to put people in charge of their personal finances – firstly by giving them access to their credit score and report, then by teaching them how to understand and improve it. The business was recently awarded a place on the prestigious Future Fifty list and we have ambitions to reach over 12 million users globally by the end of 2019. We launched in South Africa in 2017, in India in 2018 and have more markets on the roadmap for 2019 and beyond. As an analyst for the Australia team, you’ll be focussed on helping us to bring on as many new users as possible, understand the user base and work out how we can best serve them. The insights you uncover will shape the strategy. You’ll be looking at questions such as...  How do we make our media spend as effective as possible? What features do our users find most helpful, and what more can we do? How do we ensure that our users can apply for credit as simply, quickly and safely as possible?  You’ll be working as part of and getting support from the wider new markets team (mostly UK-based) and the local market team out in Australia, with the chance to travel out to London, Mumbai and to our other markets. The ideal person will come with a natural curiosity and analytical nature. You’ll love learning, have a go-getting attitude and a willingness to think creatively. You’ll enjoy the fast pace and the ability to get things done. What we would like you to do:  Be a part of a small, close knit team working on a wide range of activities to drive growth across the Australian business. Get involved in the decision and insight analytics across the Australian and international team, focused on user signup, engagement and monetisation. You don’t need to have experience in all these areas, but we want you to enjoy the chance to learn on the job. Have an open communication style as you work with other teams around the business and around the world. You’ll be able to take the initiative in spotting issues and opportunities, digging into them, and understanding how they impact on the business. You’ll be able to work closely with developers, product managers and marketing and commercial teams to really understand what’s going on.  Requirements  1-2 years analytical work experience Comfortable using SQL Ability to deliver key findings to the business in a clear and concise manner Good written and presenting skills Numerate with a good attention to detail Experience with R or Python is a plus  Benefits  Holidays – 24 paid holidays and a “duvet day” on your birthday 9.5% Super annuation Flexible work hours and the ability to work from home Flexible, generous and personalised maternity and paternity plans Monthly team events and office days out that we get to choose, and company events at the end of each race and retro

Digitas, Sydney Australia - Data Analyst Digitas is a highly-caffeinated playground where brilliant minds come together to bring bold, award-winning ideas to life. The Data & Analysis team uses data-driven insights to fuel strategic growth for clients. They are currently recruiting an AO6 Senior Information and Data Management Officer for an initial 12 month contract period.  The primary responsibility of this role is to lead the maintenance and documentation of spatial and attribute data, supporting impact assessment through emerging data-analytic techniques for business improvements.  The successful candidate will be encouraged to continue to develop their skills through training and development opportunities as part of the role.  The Senior Information and Data Management Officer will be responsible for: Collation, analysis and interpretation of groundwater-related spatial and attribute data to support scientific assessment.Maintaining awareness of and applying emerging data-analytic techniques to ensure efficient manipulation and use of large regional data sets and converting data into information.Supporting the development, maintenance and use of data-management systems for storing and manipulating spatial and attribute data.Providing ongoing support for the ESRI suite of software.Preparing maps, digital illustrations, documents, presentations and reports for a range of stakeholders, related to spatial and attribute data.Liaising with internal and external stakeholders to identify and incorporate data and information necessary for use in spatial applications. It is desirable that the successful candidate will possess: High level skills in relevant spatial information systems and/or data-analytic techniquesExperience in data management in groundwater or mining applications, andWhile not mandatory, it would be preferable for the applicant to have relevant qualifications in geospatial information. Additionally they will demonstrate strong oral/written communication, presentation and interpersonal skills. They will display initiative, attention to detail, and have the ability to work autonomously and unsupervised whilst contributing to the wider team's objectives of ensuring service delivery exceeds expectations.  Apply by clicking onto the "Apply" button. Please submit a resume and covering letter outlining relevant experience as part of your application.  For a confidential discussion of this opportunity, please do not hesitate to contact James Chapman on 07 3031 3220 or email [email protected]  skills Geospatial   qualification geospatial Information qualifications   educational requirements  Bachelor Degree

Job_Title: Head of Data Strategy | Ad-Tech | Brisbane HQ
Description: A position is open for a Data Strategy Lead to join a well-established Ad-Tech company in Brisbane. Rubix has partnered with one of Australia's fastest growing ad-technology companies headquartered in Brisbane. The business tracks, interprets and collects data from TV broadcasts, servicing Networks, Brands and Agencies Australia-wide. As Data Strategy Lead, you'll be part of a cross-functional team of problem-solvers and creative thinkers, putting people at the centre of their work. You will have overarching responsibility for the interpretation of data with the main goal of delivering tangible outcomes for their clients. Furthermore, you will identify and drive innovative applications of the data that will benefit clients as well as the "growing accountability and optimisation through knowledge" industry within which they operate. You'll work closely with clients, industry partners, research specialists and will be at the forefront of demonstrating how emerging technologies serve to enhance marketing communication strategies for both traditional and emerging media channels. In this position, research, experimentation and diverse thinking are just as crucial as delivering fast, incremental insights via a test, learn, refine model. Working with clients to progress their marketing strategies, with the main goal of enabling clients to improve their business outcomes. You'll work with a team of professionals to identify insights and opportunities, working closely with the engineering team to implement data driven solutions. You'll leverage experience with data manipulation and statistics to understand the clients' goals and challenges. You'll identify key areas of opportunity, performing analysis and modelling to assist in doing so. This includes the clients web properties across multiple device and channel communications (website, EDM, Search, Display, and Social Advertising) as well as their office data for marketing purposes. This individual will then communicate their findings in a clear and valuable way, ensuring continued success for the clients' experience.  Key responsibilities:  Partner closely with clients to understand their business challenges and develop appropriate analytics, reporting and visualisation solutions allowing them to connect media investment to business outcomes Create and drive measurement test and learn programs for clients to increase effectiveness understanding at a both geo and/or channel level Take broad business questions, developing engaging briefs and translating them to a clearly structured approach Develop new ways of looking at data - keeping creativity at the core   Requirements:  Solve problems and provide business insights and recommendations from multiple and often disparate data sets Deliver data targeting strategies, managing data purchasing processing and delivery Highly analytical, experience in developing dashboards, illustrating campaign effectiveness, customer profiling and modelling/segmentation You'll have been in a client-facing role beforehand You'll know how to develop statistically robust test and learn strategies within multiple communication channels Strong understanding of digital marketing channels and database platforms and be confident talking to clients about what is possible in personalised, customer led and real time engagement Excel in presenting complex data and information to technical and non-technical audiences   I would love to discuss the role in depth with suitable candidates, so please contact Chloe Haywood on 0403 763 772 or email [email protected] We welcome Australian citizens and permanent residents of Australia to apply, and all those will full working rights.
